LWAYS overcharged!!\n\nThe first time I brought that to their attention, it was corrected, but the last time, I was overcharged by $263, and I was getting the run around by two specific employees there, Ms Shannon, and Ms Jenna.\n\nThey try to belittle you, and make faces, because you are questioning their billing practices, and they don’t want to return your own money, back to you!!\n\nBut, everyone must check their EXPLANATION OF BENEFITS (EOB), and contact their own insurance company, and have them explain what it means.\nAfter that, it’s just doing the math.\nPlease do this, and don’t let them tell you it’s the insurance’s fault, because they keep using “different fee schedules”!!!!\n\nRemember, YOU purchased the insurance!!\nAnd it’s there for YOUR benefit, not the Dr’s office.\n\nMaria","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Maried Damiano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKr3KLxLm00ESYR0BB6HrdQy1Edd_b0Tz6JWJEeVfRgphqrDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband had his appointment with Texas Dental 11/20/25. After three years, My husband (Edwin Mangaya)decided to go back with Texas Dental. We had our experienced from other dental clinics, They are not friendly, honest, their job performance are not as good as Texas Dental. My husband was so pleased to his hygienist was wonderful (he couldn't remember his name) But over-all, dentist doctors and staff was very respectful and friendly. Facility were kept well cleaned. Will definitely recommend to our family and friends...","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Valerie Lopez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ2o4qdfsW3wDOxnv6PKkSwPduGRV1Tb3Qq_e3jTdh73Gl3Bg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️\nI can't recommend Mrs. Trevino enough! Over the past 7 months, she has been absolutely amazing with all the work I needed. 🦷✨ She was incredibly patient, kind, and very understanding throughout the entire process. 😊💖 The entire staff at the office was also outstanding—friendly, professional, and welcoming! 🙌🏽🩺 Thank you all for taking such great care of me! Highly recommend! 🌟👏","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Princess County","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvrXJYftC9pBzWLhiHpfNl5G__7igT3R5p-Up-SAhJa4WsHgOrEw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very pleased with Dr. Trevino all the people they are so nice. The doctor gave me a thorough teeth cleaning. She explained to me what she was doing also ask ? On how I was feeling . I was very pleased with my cleaning. My mouth didn’t really hurt on the right side. I’ll be going back now couple of weeks to get the left  side done.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rosa Kunstmann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKX6DccU3rBOEq9FXlUuyh9RWtaG9UE6u3elggkcSKRju3XnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The staff is very friendly and treats you with high respect. Everything is very clean and covered in plastic. To avoid cross contamination. Haven’t seen a dentist office that clean and equipped with top technology.\nDr. Miranda and her assistant Kathryn, were very communicative. They informed me about everything and what the next steps will be.\nDr. Miranda was the first and only dentist who pointed out that I still had one of my baby teeth left. I’m 46 years old.\nI always had to make my dentist aware of the baby tooth.\nVery impressed. Thank you for a wonderful first visit.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Debbie Kruciak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiD4HMINoExhGUmjB8cDue3jbMMrbLr9G7lmCRzTTBXYasPg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had cleaning an x-rays Monday at texas Dental. Dr Miranda was wonderful and chipper as usual, except for telling me it’s time for more dental work. Mario gave me the best cleaning yet. He just keeps getting better and better.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Angelina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbWEynDjguHovZuInmr8enpmJfuvRxwucjOSU7_aHKaKRhi5x8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have been to this dentist office three times, I have a chip on my front tooth and had to get composite bonding done.\nThe dentist looked a bit young, like she had just finished school so I am assuming that she will get better with time but when she was doing the bond I was in pain and she didn’t really check in with me to give my mouth a break.\nI have severe TMJ and it is a challenge to keep my mouth open, it was open for about an hour straight.\nI do not recommend this office due to the lack of care from the doctor and the incompetence that comes from the workers at the front desk.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Belle Son","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIIR2ZwsHqt2w-ovbOLXb_H8ItR7vMIvXHN0gzipFF1_diWzbktQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The dental assistant and dentist Mrs. Ha were the sweetest, gentle, most friendly people I’ve encountered at a dental office. The facility was beautiful and everyone else helped me with ease and understanding of my insurance situation. Definitely recommending all of my family and friends to Texas Dental! Thank you all so much!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
