some and ordered some more medication! Offered to see me in his office as soon as weather gets better! Hopefully it will resolve the issue ! Once it does, I will update this review again !\n\nMy rating is for his quick response and ability to be available!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Richard Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK641Ffuj1M8bbYG_B_jRhRS72CSTG80oBJcxKE8pIS9MoKLQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolute worst dental experience I have ever had. I am newly relocated to the Sanger area. Saw their office and called to make an appt to have my teeth cleaned. I have absolutely no dental issues. They sent me the usual web link to complete all the detail it seems like any doc or dentist wants these days, essentially your entire medical history. And it of course included detailed insurance information. I spent 30+ minutes completing everything. I arrive today and first question, we need your insurance. I told her they have it. She said they did not. That was the first red flag, their procedures there are obviously terribly mismanaged. So I fortunately brought my insurance and gave it to her. Then they wanted to perform a standard xray panel. Ok that's fine my insurance will cover it. The tech told me that is all they would need. Then they tell me they need more xrays and they cannot confirm my insurance would cover it because I didn't provide it. By this time I had lost all patience, they were the ones that totally dropped the ball and should have had all my insurance coverage verified before I walked in the door. But they could care less about that aspect as 100% of their intent was centered around trying to throw the blame back on me, that I was being difficult to deal with. I of course know that its not a pretty picture when an insurance company doesn't cover your medical or dental expenses and was only trying to protect myself. Long story short after an hour and a half of them continuing to try to upsell me on everything I told them I was leaving. Never got my teeth cleaned. This was completely mishandled and mismanaged from the moment I stepped in the door. I would of course never recommend going there but if you do and are a new patient make absolutely sure they do all their insurance verifications upfront before you arrive. Because 100% of their business model is upselling.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nilsa Corporan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVh8Tk5JDjdb7VdggV1x-AwYHvca4otCoVeZuwpFIl5KmNjqro=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️\nA+ dental implant experience with Dr. Julio Rodriguez \u0026 North Texas Family Dental\n\nI can’t say enough good things about my dental implant journey with Dr. Julio Rodriguez and the team at North Texas Family Dental. From my first consult until now, they made a big, scary process feel totally manageable—and even comfortable.\n\nConsult \u0026 Planning:\nDr. Rodriguez and his staff took time to explain every step, answer all my questions, and walk me through the timeline and costs up front. No pressure, no surprises—just clear options and what to expect.\n\nSurgery Day:\nThe office was spotless and calming. The team checked on me constantly, made sure I was numb and comfortable, and talked me through each stage. The procedure was much easier than I expected, and they sent me home with simple aftercare instructions that actually worked.\n\nFollow-Up \u0026 Healing:\nThey checked in after my appointment and were quick to respond when I had a couple of “Is this normal?” questions. My healing was smooth, and I never felt rushed at any visit. Scheduling was flexible, and I always felt like a priority. Office staff is amazing and always so pleasant.\n\nBottom line:\nIf you’re nervous about implants, go see Dr. Rodriguez. He’s skilled, gentle, and genuinely cares. The whole team is professional, friendly, and organized. I’d give them more than five stars if I could. Highly recommend!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2Xb0qq9274Xc7aukxEmXIxT8ZVLzNri1aS09DTvrnWBd3HHfq2ayx5GjGZQ4Iey7OtWmTqnjtUBkN8Zhc0N33nWNIkmn1F8uv2_gVtAvrZIdNKSXoIKqQXAOzGJU_6Vx_aO-CUlkAc5ad3=k-no"],"When":"2025-9-5"},{"Name":"Martin Griffith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJI5VwMsOQSfgq_0PONjWtALO9YaSgyNBoD4Ze7hRL6NVC3Sg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fantastic Dental Clinic. Certainly worth the drive to Sanger from anywhere in North Texas. Doctor Khan is a very caring and professional in dealing with patients. He takes whatever is needed for the patient to understand their dental needs and a progressive program to resolve all issues. His staff from the front office to include Dr Rodrigues, oral Surgeon, the dental assistants and hygienists are all very professional and extremely friendly to all patients. I am speaking first hand about this clinic and state plainly….it is the best period.\nI am a professional retired manager with years of experience dealing with other dental clinics and none can compare","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jennifer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWoTjceYbcRgiKZkYFb0Z0q6nWGTQod0p7BIMJdeabyhPWsxe-vMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The response to my initial message was immediate and I was offered a free consultation appointment for the next day.  I am very impressed with the staff members.  They took the time to answer| all of my questions and explain everything and I have a complicated case.  They discussed financing options and Wendy went through the whole treatment plan and helped me figure out how I can finally have crowns on my implant posts!  I appreciate all you did Wendy you are amazing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"George Riojas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI9xyIuAisTdOeZLQu-wdPvgLXT2YtOQUZsmMxsdb6-XPR03w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have to say, great people, great service, awesome service, they explained everything they were doing! I highly recommend this place. Thanks for the great service I received, also great staff at the front desk, Thank you all for the awesome service!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"A W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlRiqboN0pcjGEkhEFT3QcRd1ttyE1t_VSI2IFEjzDGqlK6yI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"They attempted to charge me twice for the same fillings, and only corrected it after I showed proof of payment. The dentist also didn’t offer different treatment options, just the most expensive one. When I asked about a more suitable and less costly alternative (metal crown vs porcelain crown), they refused, saying I had already agreed to the pricier choice. The dentist is not customer oriented, and I will be going elsewhere.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
