gleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=QrGyZvt6W83DkvYCORFP-w\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=105.53619\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"116686140788472596519","name":"6 to 9 Dental Texas (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116686140788472596519"},"complete_address":{"borough":"South Side","street":"2603 SE Military Dr Ste 103","city":"San Antonio","postal_code":"78223","state":"Texas","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true},{"name":"Language assistance","enabled":false}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Gender-neutral restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Britt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKmdpgqaC9G6ZLAtIADZhk0LfZxiIcUf5b7qAyo1keRcx9-9a8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Scheduled some work on my treatment plan for Thursday and I had some confusion in regard to what was being done so I called to the office to get more clarity. I know I must have sounded flustered because I WAS lol but I tell you what... Darlene and Katie handled it with so much grace, compassion, and PATIENCE! Thank you both so much! I look forward to my appointment with Doctor Barnes and being very well taken care of by the amazing team at 6 to 9 dental!\n\nSide note! I researched and researched and RESEARCHED before I chose this dental office. I have insurance and I saw they took it, so I booked my consultation. I haven't been to the dentist in YEARS so I was scared and knew I had so much work needing to be done so I was also very much embarrassed. The team made me feel so welcomed, so cared for and one of the dental assistants even cried with me over a shared experience! Please give this dental office a chance. Dr Barnes is amazing and the team/staff were so professional, welcoming, empathetic, and KIND! I can't say enough great things!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jessica Reyes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUb6dp5DUgP3ZzFrbS4TUwFPhl2ayOfI5eFvdo5ISOkqZHxIOBXg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Response to Owner: Let’s be clear: I was never an employee of your office. That assumption is flat-out wrong. And being “nice to patients” doesn’t address the real issues. That’s the bare minimum in healthcare, not a defense against legitimate concerns. The real issue is your office practices. Your inexperienced treatment coordinator Katie does not bill patients’ insurance properly and instead convinces them to apply for credit through Cherry or Sunbit, often under the guise of a discount that doesn’t actually exist. Patients deserve transparency, accurate billing, and treatment plans that reflect the care they actually receive. I strongly urge anyone visiting this office to review every bill and proposed service carefully. What I experienced isn’t a minor mistake—it’s part of a larger problem in healthcare, where patients are misled and overcharged.\n\nORIGINAL REVIEW: I’ve been a patient here for many year’s. Sadly, the office staff has been falling short in the customer service department. I walked in yesterday for my scheduled appointment and was not greeted. Of course there was someone new at the front desk as there always is. I asked for a toothbrush because I had eaten something real quick before my treatment, the front desk lady must’ve forgot because I waited 15mins and still hadn’t received a toothbrush. Then I got called back for vitals, I informed the gentleman that I was waiting on a toothbrush, he said he was going to ask an assistant to get one for me but was gone for about a minute to return and tell me “they were out”. Not his fault, he offered me mouthwash which I accepted because it was better than nothing but it seems they’ve been out of toothbrushes for some time because I didn’t receive one at my cleaning appointment either in September. Back to my appointment, the gentleman took my vitals and then sent me back to the waiting room to wait on a treatment room to open. Once in the treatment room, no one handed me the remote or offered me a blanket as they normally do and the “massage chair” was still on from the previous patient. I say “massage chair” because it did not feel like a massage, it hurt my already hurt back. Then they took vitals again because the gentleman who took them before didn’t write them down. Dr. Barnes and his assistant were GREAT and I did receive a discount on my treatment which is always helpful. I asked Katie, the treatment coordinator supervisor how the office manager Claudia was and she lied to me by telling me she was off. I spoke with her later because I have her phone number and I wanted to let her know about the issues I had experienced during my appointment and she told me she was fired almost two weeks ago! Why lie? Now because of this lie I will be requesting my records and finding another dental office. Thank God I didn’t schedule an appointment for my husband or children! Lastly, they are out of network with ALL PPO’s so keep that in mind when it comes to billing because you will pay more versus going somewhere that is “in network”. I didn’t mind this in the past because of the exceptional service I once received.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Karla Camarillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5rTc6aNzbZfVSPvXnTqsWO5GizLjj-QeuxQFSO8WBI-Bsoc9mwA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"DR. BARNES AND KARINA ARE WONDERFUL!!!\nIve never had a bad experience here, I started here as a self pay patient a few yrs ago, their prices are reasonable and they've always worked with me on payments if I needed them. But this office is 10 outta 10. From the front desk to the back! I had the pleasure of being take care of by Dr. Aaron Barnes, and he was amazing! Bedside manner was stellar! I'm a nervous wreck, like most of us, but he was so calm, kind, and understanding all while being quick, professional, and proficient in his work. His RDA, Karina was just as wonderful. She was kind, explained everything fully and so attentive. I've left a few times once I had ins and have always regretted it and return happily paying out of pocket! That's how great this facility is. The office is always clean and inviting. Genuinely will continue to come here with or without ins for as long as I can.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeffrey Clark II","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHtQ0SW6GSdZQmlQowxKOSZYi5ZATnpdXN9rnFF4wyyVSfBrC9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had another great experience at 6 to 9 Dental Texas (2603 SE Military Dr, Ste 103, San Antonio, TX 78223)! 🙌🏽\n\nDr. Barnes, along with Assistants Esperanza and Karina, took excellent care of me. This was my second emergency visit, and just like the first time, the staff was friendly, professional, and made me feel completely at ease.\n\nBig shoutout to the whole team for their kindness and quality service — 5 stars all the way! 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟\n\n👉🏽 If you’re in San Antonio and need a dentist, I highly recommend checking them out! 🦷💯","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"e r","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLv_pLtVdkpMZWEb0a-wqUAe1uvJn5cgAnyf3dBxor8jy7wcQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr.Barnes did a great job on removing my difficult wisdom tooth. He was as gentle as could be and comforting. Shout-out to staff too. Loved the laughing gas too,no more anxiety!! Also Dr.Barnes has taken care of my cleanings and fillings, definitely recommend 💯%!! -Jan.2026","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Vincent Ortiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKoC52DZpCRVF-biKt1oJ9cPrDs8-AbOgrqSbONKJaoq3UUjg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Brianna from front desk was amazing and very sweet. I felt comfortable with her knowledge and experience. She always had a smile and so professional. I will always come back and been going for over 20 years.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"KLAUDIA GONZALEZ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2XAzhq5EJ3P_Q2GJEU4SPSlgJI9H9BGMJwf0Iep38HxyVLXTx=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️\nI’m so glad to see the office under new management! While the same doctors and some familiar staff remain, the entire team truly strives for phenomenal patient care and satisfaction. From the moment I walked in, I felt positive vibes and was warmly attended to. My treatment plan was explained to me thoroughly, including my exact co-pay and out-of-pocket expenses. They even offered me a payment plan to help cover those costs. Thank you, Dr. Humphrey and Dr. Thaksr, for your patience, understanding, and outstanding care!!! Highly recommended","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cherry D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJCMPhBgDYC1pbszsCjw7t-2V3yYVUHEFwd6O_KK0Sl3O4IUQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am someone who suffers with awful dental anxiety due to terrible experiences in the past. Because of those experiences I normally will go years in between visits out of fear. HOWEVER, after my experience today with Dr. Barnes I actually felt comfortable enough to schedule a cleaning for 6 month down the road before leaving the office.\nI was made to feel extremely comfortable and cared for, no one made me feel ashamed for the amount of time it has been since I went to a dentist but made me feel relaxed and encouraged through out the experience.\nThey were very thorough with their communication about every step of the process.\n6 to 9 will definitely be my dentist moving forward, and I will recommend it to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
