patient care. The hygienist was amazing, and the dentist was knowledgeable, patient, and attentive. They made sure I was comfortable the entire visit and answered all my questions. The office is spotless and well organized. I actually look forward to coming back—something I never thought I’d say about a dentist!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dawnia Bruton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLfwhWao7uPwuuThdsAXh46bE3yIHaa4dhDl8y0A4edXwNBrA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Dr. Endsley and Evelyn, the hygienist, are both five star.  Very professional and caring.  However, I consider the front desk staff less than one star.  I have been leaving messages for various front desk staff members as well as their manager, Angel, multiple times.  I have not received a call back and after extensive hold times, I am hung up on.  I have (what should be) a very simple insurance billing question that I need an answer to.  I find it very unfortunate that I will be forced to find another dental office that has better communication skills with their patients.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chelsey Loewen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4lV2GHBZ8Mr8qjEeoXmmUtpP1vUyIc3ovTp-KZJ6ufX9cvHg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Legends dental was amazing. They got me in quickly and really took their time explaining things to me. Their X-ray machine was amazing and really elevated my level of care. I will be making Legends my forever dental practice.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"M D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK6QOysgqmnPPRZOVPGD65WXrwbtOf7Tz-GCziNIOVytOW5fQk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m consistently impressed with how easy it is to get in here. Everything from the front desk to the billing runs like clockwork, and the care is top-notch. The automated texts about appointment openings are a great touch and make scheduling cleanings around a busy, changing schedule effortless.\n\nDr. Sean Endsley is personable and direct — he doesn’t sugarcoat things — but he takes the time to explain everything in a way that makes sense. Exactly what you want in a medical professional. No surprise Legends Dental is sitting at a near-perfect Google rating (4.8) — it really speaks for itself. Five stars from me.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nikki Woycheshin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLPfP-CkEz8EGfAk7ztDFLwd8XkGmYwJjgRp9WinWV1vz8p9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been bringing my son for the last 6 years, he is almost 15 now. Everyone is so friendly and professional. Dr Endsley has always been wonderful along with the assistants and hygienists. The couple times we’ve been seen by Dr Armstrong have been  very pleasant. Such a nice atmosphere and I am happy to have found a dental office that understands our views and makes sure we are given the upmost care and respect. Thank you to all of the dentists, the dental team, and staff!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amy Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIoYvZquOk60r1ib3866fpVtLxv7o8gjZmfaNGbTzz5KyephQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely loved my first appointment at Legends. I went for a problem focused visit for a questionable spot inside my cheek that my PCP wanted me to get checked out. While there, we discussed an issue I was having with grinding my teeth and recently being diagnosed with positional vertigo.  Amy, the hygienist and Dr. Endsley were amazing at explaining the possible correlation between the two.  They immediately adjusted the height of a crown that I had done several years ago, which might have been contributing the issues I’m currently having. All of the staff were very kind and pleasant to work with.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dalia Lopez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKsBbWDe_ZDotXemtMLzeHLnI8JEOrFMPaRI0TWdQmygBu_Hw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Terrible experience here, mine and my husband's charts must've been switched. I was told I have periodontal disease, not the case. As a matter of fact, hygienist told me I have very mild plaque, no other issues. My husband asked for fluoride treatment, did not get it. Had to return to the building for it, I guess it was a good thing we had to return, that's how I found out about the mix up.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Robert Matlock","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKW2ebe8Ok51xprXHQnmc3FV3JvCCu6ZhYIx04pMLEOWhLnyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They got me in the same day and were able to reassure me.  Great staff and Dr Armstrong’s expertise was appreciated!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
