4t_okvvh75hVZeJOPBMivgDnsrb7E1CT7POrjiA3M=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-20"},{"Name":"Lindsay Harrell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWmFcFPIQonv8aLcUYbF4ONU87rRQf_O790F7WEkD9cgHMM-kDlwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can’t say enough good things about this dental office. The atmosphere is warm and inviting, and they genuinely care about making you feel comfortable. The staff is incredibly welcoming and professional. Tracy and Natalie at the front desk deserve special recognition—they have been amazing and have helped me so much every step of the way during my dental journey. Their kindness, patience, and support really stand out. I highly recommend this office to anyone looking for great dental care!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jess Caudle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW99hNRBwZuvuoZ0m_U1dEl0-z6tJ4k2gU4j-eQhXKzxK4O9hA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is amazing. This was my favorite dentist experience ever. I was amazed at how well they took care of me. I told them I was leaving the country soon, but they didn’t have any openings before then. So they kept me in the loop on cancellations and worked me in. When you arrive, they give you tour of the whole place and then give you a dry erase board with a long list of amenities so you can select what you want to make you more comfortable. Incredible service. Addison, the dental hygienist, was so patient and kind and did an amazing job. Dr. Hillstrom actually took time to get to know me and answer my questions. From the first call to the end of the visit, I felt like a queen. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Riley Skillman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqb1o1DQZs6HCmTt7I1kbByizIRsVPgc0L0y4XLaXInu446g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This office is incredible. The front desk team deserves a special shoutout!! they are warm, welcoming, and extremely efficient. No long waits, no confusion, just smooth and professional service from start to finish. They make what could be a stressful appointment feel easy and comfortable. It’s clear they truly care about their patients. I wouldn’t go anywhere else!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Deqwana","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHHZbZQyfYUy6lroaBssJ-tr8ZwlpColttUKqhGyDxzZOVq48=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had such a great experience at North Texas Dental Associates in Plano! From start to finish, Carolise (spell check) was incredibly welcoming and kind… she made me feel completely at ease. Her warmth and attention to detail truly stood out, and she provided exceptional care throughout my visit.\n\nDr. Ross was equally amazing… calm, gentle, and professional. During my extraction, both he and Carolise made sure I was comfortable every step of the way, checking in often and explaining everything clearly.\n\nIt’s rare to find a dental team that combines skill with genuine compassion, but they absolutely do. I left feeling well cared for and grateful. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Taylor Dickerson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJDmjUG0r6Lcgoi5kk2zFX47Hw7CLs9WDISJjxwWdK45Km4KQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an all-around great experience here. The staff is so wonderful and friendly. Linsey did a perfect job on my cleaning. It was quick and pain free!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sonia Moreno","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJYtIa5AUPrOsIRtEOfoNSMxnIx5E7P5GArFb4Ark2qYz-BZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had yesterday on November 6 , 2025 a very embarrassing and unpleasant experience with the office manager. She never even introduced herself before accusing me of owing them over $1,000 — which was completely incorrect. I immediately tried to explain that I had already paid in November 2024 for my two dental crowns, but she kept repeating that there was no record of any payment.\n\nThis all happened in front of other patients, which was humiliating and stressful, especially knowing I was right. At one point, I mentioned that I had just paid $5,000 for an upcoming surgery, and her response was, “Oh, congratulations.” I found that comment incredibly insensitive and unprofessional, given the seriousness of my situation. I said is nothing to congratulate me for a mayor back surgery, and she responded oh well my husband has one of those .\n\nEventually, I told her to call me once she had proper documentation showing that I owed anything and left the office. About twenty minutes later, I received a call from Stacy letting me know that it had been a mistake and that I didn’t owe anything after all. The least the manager could have done was to call me herself and apologize for her behavior.\n\nBecause of this experience, I will never return to this office. No patient should have to deal with that level of disrespect or lack of professionalism.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kawata Family","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJKk784dC-E6I1RWvkOVFXiZiTI7k-MxARxKPzq0-mNuokRREM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Prettiest and cleanest dental office! I’ve been going here and now my husband goes too. I recently took my two boys, both middle school age, here and they both had a great experience and said how nice everything was.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
