id":"ChIJS0xI8jHmS4YRE82KyCxyPMg","images":[{"title":"All","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHqca0i8dI8HLoGgF1EXeoOnGgY6NSAiGFu_8jUZIB201fYNmD8sFf5z63Gf81XjlnfGbkOYFnPahXO5Q7bVG6vFoM7S_wdhSJD-S7hcmLETpVgDU-q9CWSU8hS4d7GO9Nqvagx3g=w447-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHmsBDViyNG9KlIRxkOHQ2UR38cY_aA_5Cy9rFOxhPHiLplkLw6UrdOVWVOrLBaNG3W2LRce_1EgjBzVkjpMRQR4ZfjVhS6qPad3Q2AGGieI523vdoFfSVKwGAmAt-t-zonLVyJ=w447-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=7jzj1XZWdjUOqgc_6udiUw\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=4.0692744\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"112470726026706249102","name":"Texas Tiny Teeth Pediatric Dentistry \u0026 Orthodontics Greenville (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112470726026706249102"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"5605 Sayle St","city":"Greenville","postal_code":"75402","state":"Texas","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Pediatric care","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Mo E.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHGstdpK3oZKy-vs_Zd6JV8iIe9wbQwPpJG5M8APwge9LTgQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We’re so happy we found Texas Tiny Teeth in Greenville. The facility is very clean and thoughtfully designed. They have a fun kids’ zone that helps keep our little ones busy and not focused on why they are there. The staff is always friendly and welcoming at every visit. We also love that there is plenty of space in the lobby, and the kids really enjoy the movies playing. The receptionist and assistants are attentive and informative from check-in to check-out.\n\nAt times, I do feel that portions of the appointment with the dentist can feel a little rushed, but overall, they are professional and make my kids feel comfortable. Whoever decided to include the Ms. Pac-Man game in the play area is a genius! My daughter asks when her next visit is every time we leave.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jennifer Govea","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKeJ2pFRk74E2_yejRDazaySxJAbEy7UeQDosWxOlpqZsqo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My son is very afraid of dentists after a treatment in a pediatric dentist at a different location. After explanation, all the staff in the back were SO patient with him \u0026 so sweet. You can tell they treat the patients with so much kindness and patience and thoroughly explain step by step to them. They are so calm too, We love it here!!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Debra Bolden","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQLvCfCOl2G7MEPU4RcQOpr2xwlWQ3GNNWRjmavcKp3lN-bUL7GQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was our first time at this location and also the first time my daughters have switched dentists. Because of the convenience of the location, I decided to give them a try — and I’m so happy that I did!\n\nFrom Emily at the very beginning, to the amazing assistants Marissa and Yatziri, and even the front desk staff — everyone was incredibly helpful and welcoming. They answered all of my questions for both of my girls and truly put them at ease.\n\nI walked out feeling so confident and happy about our decision to switch. We’re looking forward to having this team take care of my girls’ future smiles!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"RA'MIAJ WILSON","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1fo7A9vdEeEQ_dD5Ugcud0isqAhHq--kADTFOKQfER2Du2AAe=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Esme \u0026 Dr. Patel were wonderful with my kids \u0026 very thorough. They made sure I was aware of everything throughout the entire appointment. I’ve never had a bad experience with them. Adria was great as well!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Trish Harris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWWui-YFW4ZJVKVFT28ANzmSoVYDe6t2AwcoPJNJkG-e_r4KMj-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Adria was amazing with my daughter. Thought we needed a full extraction but she listened to us and wiggled the tooth slightly and got it out quick. She used a little numbing gel but we didn’t have to use nitrous and that’s what scared my daughter the most. I really appreciate how she listened to all our concerns and took over. In and out within about 5 minutes","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kayla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUu3GaFHN74LYi-3fmS4J-NDQwZusgwCG5k4vYEbmYSj3Ms8Pkv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am a mom of 2 nonverbal autistic boys. The staff is very understanding of their specific needs. They made my boys comfortable and we made progress from their previous dental visits elsewhere. I highly appreciate and recommend this place. We will make this our home for all dental needs in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Analisa Winchester","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJavi2hEYsfu7lqjSeM7BYMMnv7eMKO2H_r1EMv90nnB9Vqjw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The assistants Mychelle, Sierra, and Esme were friendly and Dr.Patel was thorough at our first and second appointments. We were seen by Dr.K today and was slightly less impressed as she didn't introduce herself or seem very clear on the treatment planned when she came in. She initially commenting on doing sealants which had not been charted at either appointment which isn't a big deal as I'm all for preventative treatment but when the appointment was actually for the remaining SSCs it didn't seem like she was as prepared as our previous visits. Marissa who we've spoken to on the phone has always been very helpful arranging the appointments and we had a smooth check in each visit.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elizabeth McGuire","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxYOzhohPgp7mQIhj5EDCZhLXAzFJQP9Sv0X5m7jZk0JU7fmg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I am honestly surprised that this place has received more than 2 stars. Maybe some parents had a different assistant help them, or maybe they didn’t even go to the back with their child.\nI was out of work and had to use Medicaid for my daughter to get a checkup. At this time we were not able to use our dentist in Rockwall.\nThe inside of this place looks great, yes. However, the dental assistant my daughter had working on her teeth was extremely rude, pushy, and forceful.\nWhen my 5 year old daughter did not like the type of product they were using in her mouth because it “burned” the assistant became very forceful and rushing. Like she didn’t have time for my child, or even patience for the situation. It felt like because my child did not like one thing, the assistant had had enough, and needed to get to her next appointment/paycheck. Grant you, at this point we were only there for like 5-8 min tops. Then she proceeded to threaten my 5 year old that “if you do not lay down at let me finish, then your mom will have to leave and you do it alone”. I was appalled honestly. I have never left my child alone with another person that i do not know. Dr / assistant or not. This assistant decided we were not worth her time and had another one come and help my daughter instead. Which would have probably worked (because the next assistant was very polite) but unfortunately the first one had ruined it for her.\nI also had my 4 month old with me who had a couple of scratches on her head because of her fingernails (which happens from time to time with babies - obviously) but the woman at check out “asked” my 4 month old “oh baby you’re all bruised up, what happened? Did you fall off of something?”\nLike what is the problem with this judge mental place?\nShe made it seem like a cps claim was needed.\n\nLuckily enough i dont NEED Medicaid like some other people do, and that is very unfortunate. Because people that have no other option but to use Medicaid are stuck with businesses like these, being treated less than.\nIm happy that some parents have a good review, but I’ve witnessed that most send their children back with a dental assistant alone. And not every child will give their parent the full story.\n\nIf you have a choice, go elsewhere, maybe even to Rockwall for better care if Medicaid and transportation allow it.\nThis is a 100% honest review.\nI Pray people do not get treated like my kids did.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
