ating":5,"Description":"I was highly impressed by both receptionist on the 2 days in the office. Each of them were extremely professional, friendly and knowledgeable of their jobs. I was so impressed I did stop her from her duties a few seconds in private, to let her know about my observations. From her reaction, she isn't told that nearly enough.\nEven though they were careful not to say names, it would have been better for them and your waiting patients if you had a glass window for privacy insulted.\nI loved the doctor. He made me feel welcomed and interested I felt my needs were being met.\nI'm glad I finally found you.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2jyjdXvHphcF7L2eYxq9nqXvAwf2dLaU1_5FU45fFou9A4LFigXyUf2NyOnkGtz-XADu0J2GZ4Rv4GhV5FDNr5Sj5wj0LN6VfxM7ql9M_JqEhGPTHLqRyNksQuO-2sL0Mdzwk3zeHF-Si9=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0qX6RHZdWazRJ-csV9LXcalMXKAhmi0xw5Wafw4RKn8roTiD6fEuJj9D4B7Qz5Te_cT-euYAb5BDTbtse2M1taAgHEVzyb6PHSCPQDw3MQ0BSMXVOJVzCQsthAU-oKT_kDWD9VAkdp3g9N=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-10"},{"Name":"Jillian Spoor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKFW8J2L2YufZxFpXIiUBsW6z92GNeUxtoLrFwQt9pw7TnN3Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I arrived at my appointment under the impression that it was for a routine cleaning. I’ve been trying to get this done since early December when I had been given an appt. reminder card. I went to that appointment and was told they didn’t have me in the system and that if I wasn’t receiving reminder text messages, I should have known I didn’t have an appointment. 😠 Yesterday the technician said she didn’t have me scheduled for a cleaning, just treatment. So I’m looking for a new dentist, not because of Dr. Lorne but because of incompetent staff. I still have that appointment card that says Dec 8th.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Christi Burkhart","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLdTydsfx-7FuA8zZy7fEWDWYAQDgwiQakCnOMSMBscdhIa1g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently started going to Abilene Dental South since I was having tooth pain and didn’t have a regular dentist and needed to be seen fast! They were really friendly and were very professional, as well as made me comfortable and addressed my tooth pain fast! And ensured I was at ease and comfortable the whole time! They took me in as a new patient and saw me within a couple days to examine and treat me, and it was no issue for them, unlike most other dentists I’ve called to work me in immediately as a new patient. The receptionist, assistants, dentists, everyone there that I encountered are very welcoming and sweet. I will not go anywhere else in the future. I am going to continue to see them regularly and become established with their office now that I found dental care (dentist)  I’m happy with! I highly recommend!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jessica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKl1nb6ySFQWTTtLozIsynZivlPnYGyCfI0rdqMxTzpS9jZYZw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolute amazing experience. The front staff were all welcoming \u0026 informative, the assistants were all working hard \u0026 keeping things moving along, the hygienists Beth \u0026 Jessica are top notch \u0026 Dr Lorne was THE VERY BEST! 5 stars! ⭐️","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cathey D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVEixLhRiJK_qM_GeFCV_3zB_ConY8Ru28kA0ZFWZnfV4N4i4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Abilene Dental Care \u0026 Orthodontics is the best! I first found Dr. Lorne shortly after moving to Abilene. I had a dental emergency - a chipped tooth. Dr. Lorne saw me immediately and fixed my tooth for me - without insisting a full exam before doing so. Because of Dr. Lorne’s compassion, I decided to entrust him with my dental care. His dental nurse, Jess, is also the best I’ve ever had. She generates warmth and calm; she works quickly and is a true professional. Dr. Lorne has also helped provide me with two fillings. He worked efficiently and everything turned out great. I trust Dr. Lorne, Jess, and the team here to take care of me.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"KaiLeigh Elliott","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLB7akW49DSIhIAyKezX70uSfNNaqVPDyuq1DQDPHjHneoPfg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I went in for a cleaning Feb 9th and the assistant addy gave me a ruff coronal polishing that left a slice in my gums on the front tooth.. Dr. Gunti came in and diagnosed cavities, did not explain me my treatment the assistant tried to explain which I felt was not her place but his. I was being set up and asked if I was receiving a cleaning and I was told that was my cleaning. I did not accept it then had to speak to a manager Jennifer L so I wasn’t billed for something I did not receive and would have to come in a week later after already taking off work otherwise I was going to have to wait till the end of April. Very unprofessional, belt rush from the minute I sat down to the minute I walked to the front was 15 minutes, Felt misunderstood with my frustration, like it was being kicked under the rug. Will not be back unfortunately after going for the past few years and getting braces done with them. The hygienist never came in, doctor didn’t clean, and I felt uneasy about them trying to bill my insurance for something I was not given","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sarah Johnston","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJr3JpUmpHqFSowym83fKL3OvH4UW-AEUBY2YAnmk4BHbrflg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"2 stars due to billing nightmare and attempts to charge balances that were not correctly billed to insurance and attempts to ignore their contractual requirements with the insurance. Almost every visit from cleanings to the 1 major service I had to call the office and insurance due to a billing issue. The kicker was trying to get me to pay the balance when they didn't include standard information insurance companies require and waited over a year to bill it - and pushed the blame on me because I didn't make sure they billed it correctly or follow up with the insurance on why they denied it for the missing information. Prior issue of services billed to my insurance that we did not have done. Now, the actual dentist and hygienist there are amazing and very good. They never pushed services that were not needed and did not attempt to push elective services. I was very happy with every bit of my experience outside of the individuals that handle billing. it is a shame the billing issues have become so frustrating that my family is actively searching for another office and it makes one wonder how many other people were charged and paid bills that were incorrectly billed and the office should have resubmitted and followed up on.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Glen Masters","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKU0aA5p36_x3-BZThcwEh7pmrIaqapi-yQ8GICn-G8Gu4v3w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been going to this dental office for over a year now and I couldn't be more pleased with the quality of service and care. The hygienist is awesome and careful, the dentist is kind and practical, and the admin ladies explain current and future treatment costs very well. I'm thankful that I found Abilene Dental Care.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
