"options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Checks","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Elizabeth Moreno","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLojXdYJ7wIgucR582ilUggUPlwqfYHzFsxHf5MRlY4mw-jOA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our whole family goes here and we absolutely love it. The team is always friendly, welcoming, and great with both adults and kids. They take the time to explain everything, make you feel comfortable, and you can truly tell they have their patients’ best interests in mind. It’s such a great feeling knowing our family is in good hands. Highly recommend for anyone looking for a dentist for the whole family!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"KVH","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLDLxuxm3ikNoySlTJIdSmDAGLcRfYWsuWR8KE6GC8VhHeyvg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"These folks are the best dentists I've been to.  Everyone in the office is so kind and helpful.  The staff is so gentle and compassionate and the work done is excellent.  They have been extremely helpful with difficult situations and work hard to listen to your goals for treatment while also educating you about the work to be done.  Communication with both the office staff and the dental staff is great with everyone working to make sure you get the best possible care.  I can't recommend them enough.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Spencer Hays","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhnZDIqgQQFXOx-0nZwXP21PVYDVpm4Oin5_j9L6D7WB_5Ayh39Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been a loyal patient at Grand Oaks Dentistry for several years, and I can't emphasize enough how much they've helped me and my family. While I know there have been some negative reviews regarding pricing, I want to share my perspective.\n\nIn my experience, they are not about upcharging or scamming; rather, they focus on preventive care that saves us from more serious dental issues down the line. They’ve always been honest with me about my treatment options and costs, and I’ve never felt pressured to accept unnecessary procedures.\n\nThe staff is incredibly friendly and supportive, making both my children and me feel comfortable during our visits. I’ve seen significant improvements in my dental health, and I truly appreciate the care they provide. I highly recommend Grand Oaks Dentistry to anyone looking for a trustworthy dentist who genuinely cares about their patients’. They are not corporate and I love that for them. They care about their patients.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn29nyd5827yjAxybVBFWm8cVg3T2TNK8Ji86JWi075OapWQKadgHL0hPu7SPXbzp_tqivASNLs_9DTwNcCyrFU1pVkBGcdCUnRtXTA8IEY9w_2bdHJwcfXcyNDlaLqV3_YGydqsDGpX4Do=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3sySw0D7K8x9nvlcd76G0YGZTcCxxCprjTddjLW-IpNeeHrBDAYrsZW1CWBMhw7ZdNmN15qSfi4ZHpH16l57NM5epTtehf2PK8IEW6W-qNJ1FZPhdf8Fmj35uOYUdML9JUcZlZCcc1ZDDT=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3zQ56aY773NhzJm7_3zMBYpG2ZatZZM4ROq3pbsd0glo_xC8ZFSJ_rtr1Bofy9vV8stWFsMFWHDMEFDhVJFjiAja2IwubpKxfLXJfcg3zecNGv2rlLu_hYhaHuL2NeXcqVBVMUBI8OhUE=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0mldi44BBay0GvSnPt2pVVkcUinaTXl08J9YuWl-UBpXux-o4fCZG4RXYlMd77fMhxder3cQrHADjMlYx1_rEJyeeBPkcmo0m3oBc38xuHBxFrOkTVFMq6SRc3vL9zUamUsXsOlStm62c=k-no"],"When":"2025-9-8"},{"Name":"K8","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIzRLEsfcZqhbe_QWEoeIFmLzzn1C1wGFn0SdGv_mQqMVVJOMY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Grand Oaks Dentistry has some of the nicest people I’ve ever encountered! Every time I’m there everyone I interact with is so kind and friendly and always willing to explain things to me. I look forward to every visit!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexa Kantzavelos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKmp5H4es9JkzhczV-4RpRy6lB2fkNhEn1FVs18IETR57rDfA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I waited to make this review after getting a second opinion. I had seen Dr. Sharma years ago after having some complications with a tooth pulling back in my hometown. She was great then, but times have changed. I went at the end of September for a new visit and cleaning after going to another dentist who was dishonest about charges and money. Turns out this office is even worse. I made the appointment and it was for 1.5 hours. I got text confirmations and then the last text said, “remember you won’t be getting your teeth cleaned today”. I called to ask why and see if I could still get a general cleaning at least because I had to take time off work just for this appointment. The receptionist told me to come in earlier and they would try.\n\nI came in for the appointment, they spent so much time taking x-rays because they had to keep retaking them after not getting it right the first few times. Dr. Sharma comes in later and starts telling me how bad my teeth and gums are and that I’m on the road to losing my teeth because of bone and gum loss. I’ve known this has been gradually developing over years so it wasn’t anything new, but her catastrophizing of the situation was really off putting. Then she said I have sleep apnea because she’s a “sleep doctor” and I needed a $250 sleep study and her expensive mouth guards. She kept saying how I have amazing insurance because of my husband’s job and I could tell immediately that this was about money for her. She spent more time talking out of her rear, when she could have spent that time getting my teeth cleaned at this appointment.\n\nInstead of a regular clean or even just a scaling they immediately said I need a deep clean. I hadn’t been to the dentist in a year, and have good general oral hygiene with brushing and flossing, but this seemed extreme. They also said after the deep clean I need 4x a year cleanings, something I’ve never had in my entire life, but all of a sudden needed here. One of her receptionists or helpers started going over my plan and I questioned why I was being charge for PPE for my 4x a year cleanings and she couldn’t answer. The dentist then says good question, insurance doesn’t cover it so the patient has to pay. PPE is a BUSINESS expense, there is no reason that charge should be put on the patient. There was also a suspicious irrigation charge that they couldn’t explain well either. Irrigation is water to me, so I’m charged $60 for them to clean my mouth with water.\n\nI decided to get a second opinion and I am so glad I did. They did a scaling and then told me I can go back to my regular 6 month cleanings. The other dentist also said that while I have gum loss, my teeth look good and they’re not going to fall out of my head, opposite of what Sharma was telling me. If you want a dentist who is going to scam you and use fear mongering, grand oaks is your place. They are not conservative in their treatment plans at all because it’s all about money for them. Places like this are the reason people do not like going to the dentist in the first place.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1aakL106dsKnrV3tDB_MN6n_9VM_m-7YtCz74blQhIMXYqHZA2lewW4N3Cfz7HMrfxEjjaPXySJGjYya_q5XcghTUCxzKHOyYZ_0_AYy5RO7q3uJFUnixxuoBW8KN_QVXt4FUU9jc3yu1z=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-23"},{"Name":"Matthew Van Buren","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVE0CYnxRrWKiCQ9HQE5F89bEgrTtQbmvm_REZYpAOU5kf38Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I highly recommend Grand Oaks Dentistry. When I needed help quick, they saw me right away. I scheduled an appointment in the evening on a Monday, and was seen Tuesday morning. The doctors and staff were all very caring and friendly. You really get the feeling that they are there for you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gail Massey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ5hKSjrbYO9nFW79SeqzJBOhzSB7qPcMukSBPP-yJjrGLdzw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I continue to be impressed with Dr. Sharma \u0026 her office staff . Dr.Sharma has done an outstanding job of helping me with a sleep apnea mouth piece . As this is a new experience for me , she has taken time to explain all that is involved \u0026 how the equipment helps . She is highly skilled , possesses excellent communication skills , \u0026  has made me feel comfortable . Her staff are friendly , welcoming \u0026 skilled . My visits go very smoothly . The office is very clean \u0026 comfortable. I give Sleep Well Austin my highest recommendation. 🤩","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Melanie McCown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJF17yIpgO92S_YW7X_oi8DWrtvqj_V61nOrEOMjSVlJDL1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent staff, beautifully clean building, everyone gives you the time you need for any questions or concerns. You may have not feeling rushed at all. I definitely recommend this dentist and dental office for your care.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
