ues with some of the materials and they have everything there in one place to handle any dental need pretty much! Sedation, oral surgery, T-scan etc! I came in before for a consult and had the same experience? Wonderful front desk staff! Snacks, drunks and massage chairs in the lobby! Doesn’t even feel like a medical center, more like home! You can tell they truly care about their patients and their healthcare, which is more than I can say about the last couple dental offices I have been to since moving to Texas. This is my new dentist moving forward! One of the best parts is they are mercury free! I was permanently disabled at 20 from an entire mouth full of mercury amalgams and they understood my issues without even having to over explain everything. I would trust these guys with my life! Even though I just walked in, they made time for me and didn’t rush me out the door. Got me scheduled for a comprehensive evaluation in less than 5 days! I was originally referred to the office from a doctor in Canada! Apparently, the quality of their service is recognized internationally as well! Great sign!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ana Ainsworth","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUy3pNtUFJci9zX_hFI-3mTi4iXTuSZ7SfOBoLk03YaCSoCpJh9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an absolutely wonderful experience at Texas Sedation Dental \u0026 Implant Center. From the moment I walked in, the staff made me feel welcomed, comfortable, and genuinely cared for. Everyone was incredibly friendly, patient, and professional, which immediately put me at ease.\n\nThe environment was calm and inviting, and the team went above and beyond to encourage me and make sure I felt confident throughout my visit. It truly made a difference and turned what could have been a stressful appointment into a positive experience.\n\nI highly recommend this office to anyone looking for compassionate care, a supportive atmosphere, and an amazing dental team. Thank you 