/gps-cs-s/APNQkAE8n4Z9cWnSDAhFZey8FCjUO-vUQw9iGra-9R6W75mdmr9Ci2duKK4oIdfYV-qcv0m_OEuF5KzE9vCY2-Zo1eEy9wZGtpYMWGrV25j8ip7IWdiiJfCOf3Gn4aQX0WO5Au4PjSeujA=w529-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAH8U20FppQqjHNPg3AYAMqK4u_cYGArd_ECBmru3qyJt2ih0ODIMoC_tBuC2Kju7vpJSq5QLb7busQpJe2RkFiehDz0A8K5bjFiUxdAurk6S9cOyB3vcV0KUQWBGO4QG8Fc6ZEK=w224-h298-k-no-pi-20-ya101.91326-ro-0-fo100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"100449938162287678705","name":"Texas Implant \u0026 Dental Center (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100449938162287678705"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"3455 Locke Ave Ste 250","city":"Fort Worth","postal_code":"76102","state":"Texas","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":false}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible seating","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Gender-neutral restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Alisha Hadley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXdZGK1OvrfLvutU8PevBTEkBMuwOcXPf6ZvvcZknuNiaCoAjOh=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Okay, so let's just talk about genuine people that love and enjoy what they do and they're good at it. Every time I've gone in there, I've always walked out smiling and always welcomed and satisfied. Five years ago during COVID I had my bottom done on all four. From Catholic Charities from the dentist I was referred to get cleaning done to the bottom implant. And from there we got a lot of info about potentially getting the top done over time. So I was experiencing some pain that was on the left side of the bottom. The first implants I had five years ago there was an infection and it was a failure. So it was really nice to find out what needed to happen and I was given an antibiotic to take care of the infection and then I came back this morning and I had the bottom redone from Dr. Damon and his crew. They're so caring that they will do anything in their power to help you in any way possible that they can. They're more than just a crew, they're family and they all communicate very well and they're always happy. If you need some implants or dental work like cleaning and an etc. I want you to go there please because you would not be dissatisfied.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Susie Honeycutt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ7EelUPoGPqL4oa9JKPYDF0o19U7C_v3eVRnhFLJ9DJ8wPCdM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From the moment you open the door you feel a calmness from the beautiful decor. Next you notice the friendly employee who welcomes you and then you begin to see that everyone working there seems genuinely happy and has a smile on their face. My dentist is Dr. Dupree and he listens attentively to my problem. Whole mouth X-rays which can be uncomfortable but not with Arthur, the dental assistant. He took so much care that I felt no discomfort. Next he had to make the casting for the trays I would use for the treatment Dupree ordered for me. Next time I came in the dental assistant was Miss Kristi and she was just as caring as Arthur. This is a long review but I am so pleased with texas Implant  and Dental Center. My teeth are very happy!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark Nibling","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQyk1P1jhj4OVPHyTSb1-knmOpZGFjEEB7JiyubE26xVGUIu6K5g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Every single person that works here is awesome! They make you feel so comfortable and make you feel \"at home\".  They are very thorough in everything from answer questions and explaining things in detail to all of the work that they do.  I've enjoyed getting to know all of them. I definitely recommend this place for ALL of your dental needs. I will never go to another dental office.  Come here and you will be so happy that you did!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Colette Stevens","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlCVdmmBI86GHgCacUsR3w7Iw4xP4piETTVgM9naKapeMMaL75=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Arthur was extremely professional and thorough regarding how the process would go. He made me feel very comfortable while explaining why your office is the one to choice. Dr. Clark made me very emotional describing what he could do for me; however the $40k price tag is out of my range right now. Totally a professional office in every area.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sandra Belmon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ0ZtNQH-q2f7CQrR7-sc0Eakn_DB8OwF0AxQFAzLtpxx86wQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am 72 years old, and the reminder system reminder system for implant is outstanding. I appreciate them texting me to remind me of my appointments. The office staff is very professional. Amanda will take her time and assist you with your insurance information. She has patience. Lynn Baker, the Hygienist, and the doctors there are a Godsend. Baker is an excellent Hygienist and very professional. I have never been comfortable going to the dentist until I attended Texas","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jim Finch","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL0roOlg9Li9m3nQb6eUh7NvSGx6Q7GlFrrLkdhhJfxYMve=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Fort Worth office is top shelf. My experience with Arthur and Doctor Hall after the surgery was comforting. Arthur is a super nice guy and very professional. He eased my mind at every follow up visit. I was a bit confused on how the new implants should fit. Dr. Hall was kind and patient with me and explained in detail what I needed. They fit great. The front office personal are also nice and welcoming.\nDon't hesitate to go to the Fort Worth office if you're considering implants. I'm extremely happy with them.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Julie Brashears","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6gOMWPPnQCCW2Ttpc55pNML5-hwBJTTPBY-YIzUREHU46JAM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everyone was very welcoming and friendly. They all made me feel very comfortable. Dr Hall was down-to-earth, friendly, and detailed what I could expect for each appointment.The whole experience was amazing. I am usually very nervous about going to the dentist, but the entire staff was very knowledgeable and seemed to like their jobs. They calmed my nerves and I am so glad I kept the appointment. I am finally feeling much happier about getting my dental work done, and actually looking forward to the following appointments and the final results.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Donna Hargrove","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSXomkjfsOnuQZvIBAWmfM_wYUSaQR2vcu9HYy-6rkaA_lR1TB=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love the super nice and friendly staff. Dr.Dupree is an excellent dentist. He always has a smile and pleasant conversation no matter how busy his day is going. He is very professional and provides great dental service.\n\nDCHTX","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
