uired","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid street parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Dennelle Walton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1pb6yMaNSTbQqDy2Sy6SqAdFMhyvby6YJ9bVtuxsugla4IvmK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I visited several dentists in 2025 while trying to find the right solution for my dental concerns, but none truly understood my goals or presented a plan that felt thoughtful and well-considered. On top of that, I also needed to find a dentist for my son. Surprisingly, Swish Dental checked every box.\n\nFrom the moment we arrived, the entire staff was warm, welcoming, and kind to both me and my son. I’ll update this review with my dentist’s name, but she was incredibly easy to talk to and took the time to create a real, personalized plan aligned with my goals. The team was accommodating, professional, and genuinely thoughtful throughout the entire experience.\n\nI was impressed by the treatment plan, the staff’s knowledge, their professionalism, and the cost. Swish Dental quoted me an excellent price for all the work I plan to complete with them, which made the decision even easier. From start to finish, the service was outstanding—I truly have nothing negative to say.\n\nI intentionally waited to write this review until after completing a procedure. I recently received crowns, and both the process and the results were amazing. The crowns are high quality, and the dentist took great care to adjust them so they fit perfectly. I’m truly glad I trusted Swish Dental with my teeth.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn24bTcw9XeB2cu_G83p5KmS_TrwmPGW5ZprosZZWY0KUJVqGPNbocbigoKNxhSMrAYEtxRTHy7feOMZo8YAS6rUcajsaQ_1zRbHdd8bq232fE8ltWi_a8wVuTnoWqBkexiohk4CQoBf5AQ=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-18"},{"Name":"Clint Duross","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXan43XPXYlzm-Cfa_6sJHuPTRjmZ7_3wiEab2CTYZSNhNxESFE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is the worst general experience I’ve ever had . From the moment you walk in the music is blaring. It doesn’t get much better when you get back to an office. There’s a sense of chaos in the entire place. I had a young assistant placed my first temporary crown, and I’m not sure how he made it into this office. He clearly had no business putting that crown on me. It was horribly done, and I told him that and they said if this one falls out, we can give you another one… who has time for that do it right the first time. I did end up having to get a second temporary crown and then when they went to place the final crown, they had an issue with their equipment and their office manager after I had been sitting there for 30 minutes doing nothing and reached out to my office to let them know where I was and why I was running behind. She barked at me to get off my phone so that they could proceed… they placed what was supposed to be the final crown and one of the assistance even looked me straight in the eyes and said it looks great. It looks wonderful. Didn’t they told me they would need to send it out to a lab to have another one remade because this one wasn’t sitting properly I told them that they knew that I would be moving out of town and even if I wasn’t again who has time to keep going back to the same office. I’ve never had to have a crown redone once let alone twice. When I got into my car, I noticed the color was completely wrong. It was a very low quality crown with the shade, not even matching. I told them that I no longer want to allow another office location of theirs to place the final crown that it didn’t matter what office they sent me to I would no longer be doing business with their company. It took them seven months. 7 months ! To process my refund at which point I was no longer working for the same company in the majority of the refund went to an insurance company. There was no longer going to be providing me care. I informed them three weeks ago that they took so long to resolve the issue that it did not resolve the issue. I should be able to go get a crown and not have to come out of pocket since I already did once and that I expected for them to pay for a crown at an office of my choosing that would do it right they said they would get back to me just like before they have not gotten back to me and once again, I’m about to leave Texas. I have given them ample time to resolve these issues. Nine months is more than enough time to fix a problem if I were you, I would run away from this place","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"morgan cunningham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSQ_E1f-w2VVnrGNgNMb6AlICllfHD9Ef60C0v4fxR4vAZMMH-=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I just switched to Swish and can’t recommend them enough. From the front desk to the hygienist and doctors, everyone is so nice and welcoming. They explain everything clearly, and they walked me through every step of my Invisalign treatment, answered all my questions, and made me feel really confident about getting started. The staff is friendly, professional, and you can tell they genuinely care about their patients. Highly recommend to anyone looking for great routine dental care or cosmetic treatment!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nick Cochrane","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrFEVXK0g91tFYl7zsYBXv-JvT6iK8JfQnJ6f7uLFX0Fn9DOwy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My dentist retired after 25 years.\nI picked Swish because it was two blocks from my house.  I loved the staff, their equipment was state of the art.  Everyone was so Proffessional, knowledgeable and nice.  I found my new dentist.  Hopefully for the next 25 years!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elizabeth Gomez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLYIJdoE6oy3xGnbm3GGEyGEIUHpUhwR3UOSAolgZwBbljmpA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Friendly staff though the only thing is they forgot to add on the fluoride service they immediately asked me pay for at check in and I had to come back and remind them after I was told I was good to go. The individual from billing could’ve also offered better customer service when discussing my treatment plan/quote. Ultimately, I would not recommend the downtown location as this is not the first time I visit and had an experience like this.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gabrielle Swenson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtrwU5C7ifEYYY_gIfwYbz-o0JF0pmIjPTL4ozO7SS93Te6zjU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I’m sharing my experience so others can make an informed decision.\n\nSince April 2025, I have been trying to resolve a billing issue related to a root canal that was performed incorrectly at Edge Endodontics. During this process, I discovered that Edge issued a refund or credit to Swish Dental Downtown instead of to me — the patient who actually paid. I was never informed that this transfer had occurred.\n\nI only learned about it after requesting receipts and financial statements, which showed over $800 in credits sent from Edge (and it appeared that additional funds may have been applied as well). When I asked Swish for a refund, I was then told the statement was incorrect and that the money actually belonged to their office.\n\nAfter communication stopped, I had to go in person to continue trying to resolve the issue. At that point, I was told they attempted to issue a refund of $478, but it was sent to a card that was not mine. I was also told they had called me, but I never received any call, voicemail, or communication.\n\nThis raises serious concerns. If more than $800 in credits were received from Edge, why was only $478 refunded? Where did the remaining funds go?\n\nI am still left asking:\n\nWhy was Edge Endodontics’ refund sent to Swish instead of directly to the patient?\n\nWhy was only a partial refund of $478 attempted when the records showed a higher credit amount?\n\nWhy was the refund processed to the wrong card without confirming with me first?\n\nThroughout this process, I have made every effort to handle this professionally and respectfully, but communication has been inconsistent and resolution has not been straightforward.\n\nPatients should not have to chase multiple offices to recover money that is owed to them. The lack of coordination, transparency, and accountability between providers has been extremely stressful, time-consuming, and concerning.\n\nI strongly recommend asking detailed questions about billing and refund policies and carefully reviewing patient experiences before choosing care.\n\nSwish Dental Downtown, I welcome the opportunity to resolve this professionally. Please issue the full refund owed directly to me using the correct payment method and provide a clear accounting of all funds received from Edge Endodontics, including where the remaining balance was applied.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jessica Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdTdvdgcboJRPGCu3tuV11ZyhFZ7QcFX2BpSzlvjfxOESaGjzEoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hygienist Cassidy was amazing! I did my deep cleaning there and it was a very enjoyable experience. She was patient, caring, and excellent at what she does. I felt great after doing it - 100% recommend.\n\nAlso shoutout to the office that plays music that girls *actually* wanna listen to.\n\nGreat vibe, music, equipment, and team. However! The treatment plan felt overly aggressive; my research suggested some steps weren’t necessary. Worth double-checking before committing!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mauricio Rodriguez Arevalo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5mNx5j3lv8TYNoK9dLVKwYVfbwj1it47yYwPLxaRDOnS9NA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I feel so grateful for choosing Swish Dental Downtown. From the moment you walk in, you feel truly cared for. I had to reschedule my appointment a couple of times, and the team was incredibly accommodating, they found the best options for me without any complaint.\n\nI went in for a small emergency, which was quickly attended to and resolved by Dr. Bekah, who also performed a full evaluation and identified some priorities I needed to address. This led to a tooth extraction and implant preparation performed by Dr. Noor, whose work was extraordinary,  completely painless and with a very fast recovery.\n\nI can confidently say that Swish Dental Downtown has an excellent team of professionals , proactive, patient, and truly focused on patient care. Their technology is outstanding.\n\nThank you, Swish Dental! Highly recommended.\n\nMauricio","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
