","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Alyse Cormier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLVujPz-dLDy85ZSNBm4HqfUhXHnANRQmlg8gmZ8wO0MZC3qQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m very grateful to have found Belterra Dental! Melissa and Ashleigh great you with a smile the moment you walk in the door. They have different drink options in the waiting room.\n\nDr. Nguyen is a great dentist and a great person; he’s super patient, explains things very well, and makes you feel at ease.\n\nDayana and Emely are great hygienist as well! They explain everything that’s going to happen very well so you feel comfortable and know what to expect. They’re very friendly, nice to chat with, and make the experience very personable. My teeth also felt the cleanest they have ever felt afterward. They even gave me a warm towel at the end! 😁\n\n10/10!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jay Fancher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLXSqUXJ66eBjFV3yU20rr2hR22dq7TSlGNu_nd-USD9wM2uQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I moved and needed a new dentist. Dr Nguyen did not try to upsell anything, and is very nice. Good cleaning and scheduled for a 6 mo follow-up. I see he does a lot of cosmetic procedures, but if you just want a dentist for preventative or routine care and cleanings, I would recommend Belterra Dental for you as well.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Townesend Turner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4mlYzHr9qPxVm-8kmpNDm1zonjUWX9NPYsFbUluBlU4wXFh4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m very thankful to have found Belterra Dental!  Check In is always a breeze with Ashley .  Emily puts you at ease with her gentle touch and kindness \u0026 will guide u through your check up.  Dr. Nguyen will make you feel at ease with his calm demeanor and confidence elevating your trust in  what he sees best for your treatment and care. Finally, Melissa is the expert in payments and is there to answer any difficult question.  A well balanced team and amazing experience every time!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pierre","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJ-NP2Z9o3mA1qklz53wcHkV1iQHcdGn7W8KHehlv9AyF4WNyAIA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an excellent experience at Belterra Dental. The staff was very professional and kind from the moment I walked in. My appointment was on time and very efficient. The dentist addressed all of my concerns thoroughly and made sure I understood my treatment options. I never felt rushed, and the entire team made me feel comfortable and well cared for. I highly recommend Belterra Dental to anyone looking for quality dental care.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Heather Kubo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJfiLwj2LtBdOUrV8io3UxffwQ4yGGB8IB2lHX0Ud6KwpXjjA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can’t say enough great things about\nDr. Nguyen and the entire team at Belterra Dental! From the moment you walk in, you’re greeted with genuine smiles and a level of care that instantly puts you at ease. Dr. Nguyen is incredibly knowledgeable, gentle, and takes the time to explain everything clearly with no rushing, no pressure, just honest and attentive care.\nThe entire staff goes above and beyond to make each visit smooth and comfortable. You can tell they truly care about their patients and take pride in their work. It’s rare to find a dental office that feels this welcoming, efficient, and professional all at once.\n\nIf you’re looking for a dentist who treats you like family and a team that makes every visit a positive experience, Belterra Dental is the place to go!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Melinda Springer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViGeRcqaqZjWulEEW_H9t8IQU2uuLb1VSwZQdaf6JuvT7dY6fT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Being a patient at Belterra Dental is an easy, comfortable experience. Everyone who works there is friendly and knowledgeable. The office is warm and pleasant and exactly what I need to feel like Im being taken care of. I would highly recommend it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sarah Irwin, RMT","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiNJuj4QQQh3Riv5F3akWlAzmfqB-V_jxZoaiFHu8a4xCXf7A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was very  happy with my first visit at Belterra Dental. Hygienist was very thorough and answered all my questions. Dr. Nguyen was also personable and answered all my questions. I felt comfortable and in good hands with experts.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rodrigo Solis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7cwOrSDnXGo8DfdUcTC3RAACRVNXAcPzZW0-eew9oOsleEIc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This was one of the most stressful and upsetting dental experiences I’ve ever had.\nOn my first visit, I asked the dentist if he could extract my wisdom teeth. He said he could not because I was “too old,” yet in the same conversation said I had the option to remove them or leave them. That contradiction alone immediately raised red flags.\nOn my second visit for a cleaning, the dental hygienist told me I needed to remove my wisdom teeth to avoid plaque buildup. When I confronted the dentist and asked him directly which was true—remove them or leave them—he looked genuinely surprised and had no clear answer. I cannot believe a licensed dentist would give such inconsistent and careless guidance. That is not a “difference of opinion,” it’s incompetence.\nThe cleaning itself cost more than a standard cleaning, and before leaving I explicitly asked how much I owed after insurance to avoid future billing problems. I paid exactly what I was told.\nMonths later, I’m contacted again and told I owe over $140 for a mouthwash. Apparently charges just keep appearing long after services are “settled.” This feels less like healthcare and more like a billing trap.\nI try to support local businesses, but this establishment is not trustworthy. Between contradictory medical advice, poor communication, and questionable billing practices, I would strongly recommend looking elsewhere.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
