ite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Gender-neutral restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Checks","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Izzy Jones","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNMVmbkQu2JoY0mGscDBhPjq_1xfAzPR51M6-ziTEgAMOe1MwFtQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love the whole team here. For about two years now I’ve been coming to Dental Care of Pflugerville, and I have nothing but positive things to say about everyone. From the moment you walk in, the receptionists like Tabitha are always warm and friendly. Gotta be honest, my hygienist is my favorite person there, but Dr. Smith is also wonderful. I typically do have a good amount of anxiety with dentist visit, but this place is over time completely eradicating that fear for me. I’ve had multiple different types of care done through this office besides just annual cleanings, and I love this clinic.\n\nThank you to all the staff who works here for being so kind, warm hearted, honest, and hard working. I feel like everyone here is a gentle soul of a person. My absolute favorite part of my visits is the stories they tell the whole time. It’s like listening to a hilarious podcast that makes me want to extend my visits just to hear how the story ends.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michelle Wilkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxotan26LKjMx7kBnnNA1bKRooYYsXCmETxw5zo24bHvNYLos=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My children and I had a checkup and cleaning appointment at your practice on January 14. Prior to scheduling this visit, I verified my insurance coverage with your office and was verbally assured that all services would be covered. Unfortunately, I did not receive this confirmation in writing.\n\nAfter the visit, I discovered that advanced technology X-rays were taken without my consent or authorization. My children and husband were present and heard me clearly confirm that only services covered by my insurance should be performed. I was never informed that these X-rays would be taken or that they would result in additional charges.\n\nI have now received a bill totaling $704. Upon receiving this bill, I contacted your office, but my concerns were not addressed. I was told that the office manager would return my call; however, I am still waiting for a response.\n\nBe careful because this place will rip you off!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alan Xu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKEgSCcMqSGXm6Hqv9fFW8sg-4QZJFG7q1tIueD6HZt8ARCisor=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lisa the hygienist was very skilled, knowledgeable, detail oriented, and very pleasant throughout my routine cleaning!\n\nThey use new stuff like the teeth scanner typical of Invisalign, although pano might be an older machine.\n\nI also appreciated the live call for confirmation since I could ask for other times immediately without calling back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Denise List","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIPjDTVo8EmGSXVN3lpxONPsyLGH5N8Aa00t7SKVwaoa3Xqzg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I became a new patient if Pflugerville Dental in January 2026.  I had been searching for a dental hygienist that could clean sensitive teeth.  Lisa was very helpful and did an excellent job in cleaning with no pain for my sensitivity.  I’m very pleased with the care and concern for my sensitive teeth issues.  Thanks!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark Carter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI9Q3gYZbXB8lXn9CofSaAr0Tj42oa_etf3vhlaS2mi6dRtCg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I’ve been going to this dental office for the past few years because I wanted to support a POC dentist and he’s been absolutely wonderful! My hygienist has also always been amazing. However, the front desk and billing staff are a completely different story.\n\nThe customer service from that department is consistently poor. The staff who handle billing and answer the phones make it feel like you’re bothering them when you call with questions. For example, a few months ago, I received a random bill and had to call multiple times just to get a response. When I finally reached someone, they told me they didn’t know why I was being billed and needed to check with their accountant. They promised a callback, but months went by, and I never heard back.\n\nThen this week, I received another unexplained bill. When I called again for clarification, the representative was dismissive and rude, talking over me and saying, “Well, I’m not the person you spoke to, so I can’t speak for them.” The lack of communication and professionalism was very disappointing.\n\nUnfortunately, because of the repeated poor interactions with the front desk and billing department, I’ve decided to leave this dental office. I truly hope ownership or management sees this review and provides proper customer service training, because the way the staff currently communicate with patients is unacceptable","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"AKT2809","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRHGGJl0aahfnwukb9StJxleAFaB9NaywzupBqvUczFang0A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Smith is absolutely amazing! He is incredibly knowledgeable, has extensive experience, and is very meticulous about his work. I’ve been so happy with his care and fully trust him. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bret Fendt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJaYhEAm4wqkaEoHXsZxBZhw1Fp3Wv77lKkUGtaaac-iQnhyg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I feel as though two stars may be generous.  In the last four visits, I have seen four different dental hygienists, and the consistency of service continues to decline. At one point, I felt as though this location cared about my dental health and me as a person.  Over the last year that has certainly changed.  Consultations with the dentist, no longer happen, I cannot be advised as to progress being made regarding gum health, and overall care seems to have gone away.  I had been visiting on a periodontal plan to help with gum disease and my most recent visit my dental hygienist knew nothing of this treatment plan.  Well, I did receive a routine cleaning. I have no idea as to the overall health of my teeth or gums after visiting this dentist office.  I cannot recommend this location to new patients and hope existing patients have better experiences than I have had. I will not be returning and will be seeking a new dentist for future service","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Stephen Sheffield","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLdUj-E2U12nBRYKLLT79NdVIQE8Ek9DJcwW0bY9n4wdM1VjmMu=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have been a patient for several years.  I cannot count how many hygienists I have been treated by.  And I definitely did not see a dentist each visit.  But I was ok with just getting my teeth cleaned.  However, when my daughter needed a crown, I brought her here.  That was a HUGE mistake.  They started the process in May and now in November she still does not have a crown.   In May, the dentist shaved her tooth down and placed a temporary crown on.  The temporary dissolved.  I called and asked for an appointment, but they had none.  Two weeks later she went in for the permanent crown, but the dentist did not like the fit.  She took more pictures to send to the lab and put another temporary crown on.  We did this repeatedly until August when she left for school.   Each time the temporary would fall out and she would try to get an appointment and was always denied.  One time we walked into the office and they couldn't put a temporary on because there was not a dentist in the office that day.  (There were plenty of patients there though.)   After four attempts, I asked if I could have a refund and go somewhere else.  They refunded me $133 out of the $316 that I paid out of pocket.  They have yet to refund the over $1200 to the insurance company.  My insurance company paid them for a crown that is not in her mouth. So we will have to pay out of pocket to get the damage they caused fixed and to get a crown properly put on.  She just had a second root canal on the same tooth (perhaps because the tooth has been exposed for so long) in hopes of saving the tooth.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
