lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Gender-neutral restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid parking lot","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Ashley Geffert","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5S_SdZSeRZWJoSiCpHZxjIUoZ4l6wdhGsNTlRUTirTL8eP0LknA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely amazing experience as always! From check in with Roberto to treatment in the back, the domain team made me feel so welcomed and comfortable!  Dr. Lawson did a fantastic job, got me numb and fixed me up with my temp crown! Super quick and easy, made it a very relaxing procedure! Natalie was my dental assistant and she was phenomenal! Sahra, my hygienist, as well as Jay, and Lucero also helped make the experience very comfortable and enjoyable!! Great team here!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Richard Reed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_A0NmZnpBSsZ0eqbWuf6syMWRbS5aK0JeeWGWXe06Cb-4DUt6=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was a patient at Swish Dental for several years.  In that time, I've seen dental hygienists and dentists come and go from that place like a revolving door.  You will be told that you will require treatments whether necessary or not.\n\nIn that time, my wife's been told she's had several cavities that require fillings, only to be seen by a different dentist at the same location months later that he only saw one.\n\nMy situation was worse.  For at least a year, I was told I needed a crown for a molar with a filling that was wearing down.  I finally agreed to get the work done and paid my portion of the treatment plan.  After a couple months, Swish billing told me I owed an additional amount, because insurance denied the claim.  It was denied because the documentation Swish provided showed less than the 50% tooth decay threshold to approve.  That immediately told me I was misled by Swish Dental's staff into believing that I needed this crown right away.\n\nAfter that experience I decided to swap dentists.  During a recent check up, I mentioned sensitivity with the crown and they suggested I go back to Swish to have look at it. After an X-ray and cold test, a different dentist at Swish told me the molar next to the crown was infected and I required a root canal and crown!!!   I was blown away as I've never been told about any infection or issues with that molar until that moment.  After I was presented a $1300 treatment plan, I was told that dentist could perform that procedure later that afternoon.  I decided to pass and went back to my new dentist for a second opinion.\n\nAs expected, the new dentist told me he saw no evidence of infection with that molar.\n\nIn the end, I regret that I stayed with Swish Dental for as long as I did-- it's too corporate, unethical, and too \"sale-sy\".  If you are looking for a dentist, I would highly suggest finding a small practice that's been around for years with a stable staff and solid reviews from long time patients.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Fernanda Keeler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkGH5uWshdDoTDf8GpGu1uCZOkqUUAqiTK5f22eWMqiNO9cyvq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first visit to Swish Dental office.  Upon arrival, I was warmly greeted and sat down to wait for my initial consultation. The consultant explained all the procedures that would take place before my teeth were cleaned.  He took x-rays and explained everything shown on the pictures.  After he finished with all the explanations, the dental hygienist cleaned my teeth.  She was very thorough and professional.  I was very pleased with my visit to Swish Dental and will certainly return for my six month cleaning.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Grace Dawson Beatty","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2BnGpMj-rUlwO1f84JFriIFmO2bMczMgOaGbego2r01huYSKG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Lawson and the team at Swish Dental Domain are fantastic. Each person I interact with is always smiling, has such a positive attitude, and makes going to the dentist fun. The teeth cleanings are well done. I’m currently going through an Invisalign treatment and really appreciate how Dr Lawson and her team take the time to explain each step we’re going through in order for me to be knowledgeable about the process.\nI highly recommend this location if you’re looking for a dentist.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nathan Hernandez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLb-K-kWnGrvdQqdcZ5fUsxrULkstktzIrZPGp852POOexjhw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I had a frustrating experience at SWISH Dental (Domain location) and wanted to share in case it helps others. Also, read Reddit for more honest reviews than are here on Google.\n\nThe day before my appointment, I called specifically to schedule a routine cleaning. I clearly asked, since I’ve never been to SWISH Domain, only the Downtown location, whether I would need to repeat an exam or if I could just get my teeth cleaned, because my first visit to SWISH previously took much longer than expected. I was told I could come in for the cleaning without needing another exam.\n\nWhen I arrived for my 1:00 PM appointment, the front desk immediately recommended a fluoride treatment that was not covered by my insurance. When I declined, the response I received was, “If you can’t afford it, that makes sense,” which felt unnecessary and unprofessional.\n\nAfter waiting, staff told me they couldn’t find my information, then later said the dentist required a full new exam because I had never seen that specific doctor before. I explained I had already completed an exam with SWISH and was already in their system, but I was told it was the doctor’s policy and could not be waived.\n\nAs a result, I was unable to receive the cleaning I scheduled and spent nearly an hour traveling and waiting for an appointment that could not be completed.\n\nI called the downtown SWISH location afterward and was told this is not their standard process, and they are looking into it.\n\nOverall, the experience felt disorganized, inconsistent, and frustrating. I will be returning to the downtown office for my cleaning, but I will not be returning to the Domain location.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Noelia Root","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwORd4cLngl2ibmo_xL-BWtlIiOIhMLQk3NWdJe6Edx-IvMvRgNA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Many negative experiences to recount. If you have a better dentist in the area, please contact me, because I am up to my eyeballs with frustration with this place.\n\nThe straw that broke the camel's back was showing up this morning at 8 AM for my cleaning... and they were literally not there. No one. A temp worker of some kind was also there but had no key and told me she was told to come in today. at 8:10 I call Swish and obviously get forwarded to more central offices because no one was there at the Domain location where she told me that that were closed until 11 AM today for weather. ??? When the heck were they going to tell me who reorganized her morning and work schedule for this?\n\nThey have also twice tried to upsell me to get Invisalign. There will be times when I am told that my bite is all out of wack and causing my bottom front teeth to grind on my top ones, and if I don't do Invisalign, it will cause irreparable damage. Then, mysteriously, in my next several appointments, it is never brought up again and I will be told that my teeth look fine. I have never had braces and don't plan to, and that is only because of dentists my whole life telling me that there was no need.\n\nNot only that, but billing practices are incredibly opaque. Every time I get my bill, it goes through insurance as something completely different, or incredibly highly inflated. I have called 5+ times before to get no clarification on bills I have received with the advice always being \"just wait for it to finish the billing process\" (mind you these are from charges almost a year ago now) Not to mention how they botched my husband's cavity filling so that now he has constant pain in that tooth (never before was there any indication of pain or issues on this tooth- he filled it because they said to).\n\nStaff is kind, tech is new, and there are abundant openings. It is not all bad, but these experiences lead me to try to find a new dentist ASAP.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mikey G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL21MCw2XLjKA39SghokT4_mZ9zzayZSOzHiWO9Rj1pMJXhGA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place, very professional and nice people! Honored my insurance, and were very transparent from the time I walked into the door, from when I left. My hygienist was Billy very down to earth person, he was a pro when I came to the cleaning. Very light hand but also got my teeth very clean. The dentist was also very pleasant and professional. She gave great and honest advice. This is the best dentist office in Texas no bullshit! Thanks everyone for doing what they do.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emily T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdxTaxtDAqD00qeRCdztiQHMSwNeWEKXEybdOu9HsGTCfw8-w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"While the hygienist and dentists are great, my overall experience with assistants and office staff has felt chaotic and very disorganized. They have high expectations from us as patients, but they also expect patients to be forgiving when they’re the ones at fault. I’ll go into detail below, but the easiest way to put it is — how can Swish have a Late/Cancellation Fee for customers, but nothing happens when they miss an appointment?\n\nThe details:\n\nI was looking for a new dentist, and since the Swish Domain is near my work and had good reviews, I gave them a try. I went to get a cleaning first, and the hygienist was amazing. I needed a few fillings so I got those done as well, the dentist was amazing too. So much so that I decided to do Invisalign, but this is where things have gone wrong.\n\nI paid for the entire cost of Invisalign up front since there was a discount for doing so. But  maybe that was a mistake, because now I feel like I’m being treated as an afterthought… perhaps I should have agreed to a payment plan so that Swish would WANT to provide me the service and collect the money.\n\nMy first Invisalign appointment was January 8 where I received the first 5 trays and had attachments bonded to some of my teeth. During this appointment, they also pre-scheduled my next appointment for February 12 to get the next 5 trays and do something to cosmetically reshape some of my teeth. This fell on the exact date I’d start tray 6 which was perfect. Or so I thought.\n\nSince the January 8th appointment, it’s been a frustrating experience. I almost want to transfer the rest of my treatment somewhere else.\n\nIssue 1: about an hour after I left the first appointment, 2 attachments fell off my teeth and I had to go back to get them redone. I’ve done Invisalign before and this has never happened.\n\nIssue 2: a day later, I lost *another* attachment on a crown. This was the 3rd attachment I lost in less than 48 hours, so obviously they didn’t do something right. They couldn’t fit me in again for over a week. I had no other choice, so I made the appointment and showed up. I was there for maybe 3 minutes. They took me back, told they don’t put attachments on crowns and said “sorry for wasting your time”. I said it was fine (it wasn’t) but whatever. They said they’d see me on February 12 for my next trays and the reshaping teeth stuff. Cool.\n\nIssue 3: it’s February 12th, the day I’m supposed to get my next trays, and suddenly they DON’T HAVE AN APPOINTMENT FOR ME. Usually this wouldn’t be a huge deal, but I finished tray 5 yesterday and should be receiving tray 6 today. Of course, they’re “booked solid” and can’t schedule me until next Monday. This will effectively put my treatment a week behind schedule. The craziest thing is that if I was the one who missed this appointment, they would have charged me $50. But since they’re the ones who missed it, I’m just supposed to accept an apology as payment.\n\nI’m not sure what’s going on, but get it together. Please. Patients have to take time off of work to attend appointments. When your dental assistants do poor-quality work, it requires a patient to have to visit more frequently than should be required. Patients also have to plan for appointments. We expect the appointment we scheduled to, well, be scheduled. Your failure to properly do this and then expect us to wait for days to weeks later is a terrible customer experience. I love the hygienist (I can’t remember his name but he might be leaving soon anyway) and I love the dentist, but they’re not enough for me to stay is everyone else isn’t providing the same quality service.\n\nWhat started out to be a good experience to get me in the door now has me questioning my decision to choose Swish at the Domain.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
