98\u0026yaw=42.609848\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"111960355582203295948","name":"Dental Center of Texas (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111960355582203295948"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"23922 Cinco Village Center Blvd #100","city":"Katy","postal_code":"77494","state":"Texas","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Sonia Quintanilla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-iLSC0naav29g8I-mKZjd9J2vd8jwItvpqLqbWPGPv16kq1s=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful staff greeted me since the start of my visit. Dr. Acosta was very thorough in her examination and took her time to educate me on how to properly upkeep my dental hygiene. I’m hoping to continue working with Dr. Acosta to hopefully get some Invisalign’s to perfect my smile a step further! I would definitely recommend this office to my family and friends. Thank you for the great care!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mariela Morantes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVXWw3VRtEEOyS7davmYvddkGKoNTNu63E2pZCx9G-8n136JE0lpg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I want to thank Dr. Acosta, Dulce, and Angela for their excellent service and kindness. From the moment I arrived, I felt truly cared for. Dr. Acosta and her dental assistant Dulce speak Spanish, which helped me express exactly what I was feeling. It made a big difference, because explaining everything in English would have been much harder for me.\n\nThank you for your patience, professionalism, and compassion. Many blessings to all of you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chelsey Perkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWb0hvGnrg72rej71QNf17yV95zfF8MMH3z3E76pb1_BNtptuw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This has been an extremely disappointing and concerning experience.\nMy daughter has never had a cavity in her 18 years of life and has maintained regular 6-month cleanings and checkups. At her most recent visit, we were suddenly told she had seven cavities, all requiring fillings. This was shocking, especially given that nothing had been flagged or even mentioned at her previous visit.\nWhen I spoke with the dentist, I asked directly for a clear explanation of how this could have happened and whether any of these could be closely monitored as opposed to immediately filled. I was told that each of the cavities were indeed in need of fillings and shown X-rays (which, as a patient, I obviously rely on the dentist to interpret accurately). At that point, regardless of how we got there, we agreed to proceed with treatment.\nNow, four days after the procedure, my daughter is still in pain and I am being told after the fact that:\n•\tSome cavities were “very deep”\n•\tSome were multi-surface\n•\tSome were close to the nerve\n•\tA root canal may be needed\nThis information was not clearly communicated beforehand, despite me explicitly requesting a full explanation prior to treatment. That lack of transparency is deeply concerning.\nWhat has made this worse is the office’s handling of her records. I scheduled a second opinion due to her ongoing discomfort, and the office has refused to release her records, stating that only one person has access to them and they are unavailable for four days. I was told there is nothing they can do.\nThat is unacceptable. Patients have a right to their records, especially when there is post-procedure pain and concern about the treatment received.\nBetween:\n•\tthe sudden appearance of multiple serious cavities\n•\tlack of clear communication before deep drilling\n•\tpost-procedure pain\n•\tand refusal to release records in a timely manner\nI cannot recommend this practice. Parents should be especially cautious and ask very detailed questions before consenting to treatment.\n** Update after 2nd Opinion**\nAfter 2nd practitioner requested and was unable to receive records, they extracted what they could from the insurance company finding out what Dental Center of Texas included on their claim.  2nd practitioner mentioned that Dental Center of Texas took x-rays not meant to diagnose cavities but instead x rays designed for bones. It was determined that 2nd practitioner likely would have recommended only half of the fillings performed and instead monitored them due to the patient’s oral health history. New x-rays showed no deep drilling (thank goodness) regardless of what staff had communicated and while filling work and clean up had some sloppy elements, nothing seemed to be a risk to my daughter at the time of this exam. (sigh of relief). 5 days later, 5 phone calls, 2 texts from staff to owners, 2 emails, requests from both myself and a dentist’s office and Dental Center of Texas still will not release and send patient medical records.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Melanie Cox","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUv8HtCyyUuGmK2KeUnV4wPKqopnZrUcYHXzGL1vj3M1EkVFfe2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been coming to Dental Center of Texas Katy for more than 5yrs now \u0026 they are always so caring \u0026 gentle! I’m one of those that gets crazy nauseous before dental work but once I’m in the chair with them I’m at ease! Their front staff is always so welcoming too!! This place has changed me forever, in a good way, about getting my butt to the dentist on the regular!! 🦷","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1IeJgi-SivA8utJcWVQa9RRXd9YGew7DxsyMz9-aLVnAnq8LeJN7zYfpAH88pQN1spRAwGY0NF5rmvYv45BUbjW9H3j_ZTFnqjtp7dlQjlLzy1o-M-rPt-ZsbnqbpDJwD1m4SM=k-no"],"When":"2021-11-8"},{"Name":"nabeeha shazad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9Jz8j62aTNnxDNcA3qiaBJpiz2UQE_Dapy2NpHyn5Ivygu41xFw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This office provided a welcoming atmosphere to anyone who came in for treatment. I had such an amazing experience getting my fillings done by Dr. Acosta. Getting any dental treatment can be nerve wracking, however, Dr. Acosta made it an amazing experience freeing me from all dental anxiety! Will recommend this office to all my friends and family!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cynthia Barefield","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLlZj8u_LGVXf9Ks7oXbsl4O4GHO5bloG4uuMSKdNBL1rS8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Every one in office is very nice and helpful..\nAcknowledge you as soon as walks in the door.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeanmarie Mayfield","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-QW2iGEsjGLzd548zL7IBXcvAnhw2f-z-bj36V9B9OD7gFoaQWw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have been going to the Dental Center of Texas in Katy since 2020. We truly love the practice. Everyone is very welcoming and professional. I love that they know me by name when I come into the office and recognize my voice when I call.  I recently had two new crowns installed and the process was as good as getting new crowns can be. I really like my new crowns. I am thankful to have such a great dental practice so close to home. Thank you!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"mary wells","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtX9ZBhzw6XmUCh6gJ4N1JwGRDLMgX0Ko91ixybvI6YqyFFSBgNg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Soon after moving to Katy in 2008, Dental Center of Texas was recommended by a business associate.  The staff has remained the same with only a few changes.  The current dentist Doctor Ellis is professional AND friendly AND is sincerely caring about her patients.  Rene who coordinates everything in the office with grace and knowledge has been in the office for years.  She knows the patients and treats each individually.  The techs too are great.  The whole office seems to move along together to give superior service.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
