emove my wisdoms tooth. I was very specific that my wisdom tooth was laying down. When I went to my appointment,  the dentist told me that she can't remove it and that the specialist was available until August. And they didn't do an x-ray either. They charged me $50 for nothing. I lost my time and my money and I still with pain.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Montes S Nicholas Anthony","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyu-DdBK_oyQ1l4-9Bp_t1PKRMrun92uhqsxoQxXRqEGGaILap=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"2 stars. One star: Being that when I spoke to the doctor, he appeared to be knowledgeable in what he was doing and saying. Additionally, he seems to have the better interest of the patient.  Two Star: Convenient location. The front desk staff could be friendlier and much more efficient.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Erica Lopez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRIEcXsVSwfw-voqeCtDCSo-HbodthfAX0seN44gbJjypPCA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This place is terrible. Patients are here before the employees are. The doctor is here whenever she wants to be and they have NO CONVENIENT times or appointments. Walk ins welcome but get ready to wait 3 hours before you are seen and be prepared to listen to all the gossip in the back. VERY UNPROFESSIONAL! I would NEVER recommend this place.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
