ing","options":[{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Aduloju Oluyemi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLNiHzQArNUI3h9FaiHFL--PRgAW4oHJVUxSC_lxUSynpVNsw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a great experience at Monarch Dental in Abilene, TX. From the moment I walked in, the staff was welcoming, professional, and very kind. They took the time to explain everything clearly and made sure I was comfortable throughout my visit.\n\nThe dental team was gentle, patient, and truly cared about my comfort, which made the whole experience stress-free. The office was clean, well-organized, and ran smoothly. I really appreciated how respectful and attentive everyone was.\n\nI would definitely recommend Monarch Dental in Abilene to anyone looking for quality dental care with a friendly and caring team. They made me feel well taken care of from start to finish.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ashleigh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUY_dmACOlbnjZhiuRtypuxMOROtrFe7iL7pOiUGArjlHXbOB1RmQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The staff from the very first phone call all the way through the extractions and temporaries - have been ABSOLUTELY AMAZING!!! I have always been so nervous about dentist or procedures due to a past experience many many years ago. And from that it lead to me not getting the car I have needed for years. UNTIL NOW!!!! The staff explains everything from start to finish, step by step! If I have any questions or issue (adjustments needed) they answer with details and make sure my adjustments are just right! They pay attention to their clients and are so pleasant and cheerful throughout the process. From the moment you open the office door all the way until you leave - it’s so welcoming. You don’t feel like just “another client” but instead you feel like an individual with concerns and someone actually listening!\n\nThank You Monarch Dental for restoring my smile and giving me my confidence back!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Francisca Aduloju","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK2sn-gB-dl64htOnshYTh0MFF94AK7LKElcLeiuR_GMjWcUw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I will recommend Monarch dental over and over for their prompt and highly professional way of dealing with clients.\nFrom the receptionist to the dental assistant and the  dentist himself.They communicated well with me at every step of my visit.\nThe staffs are highly courteous and made the visit a very good one for me.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bridgette Ramos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTXXu6bwg_6hVpJrUVbzW3oDsdYCXvkVnWNn8RObHDHwfEXGTBjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This place has gone down hill in the past year. Last November I called due to needing a tooth pulled and the fastest I could be seen was 3 weeks away. I used another dentist in that time because who can wait 3 weeks for a painful tooth? I still kept my cleaning appointment because it took 3months to be seen by the hygienist in the first place. Currently I made an appointment in September for a tooth I was having issues with and again, it would take 3 weeks to be seen. I received a call back a week before the appointment just to be told the Dr. would not be in that day. We rescheduled for this Friday October 24th. I just now get a call that the Dr. will not be in again and they will have to reschedule for November 13th. This place is a joke do not waste your time. Thank goodness I had forgot to cancel anyways because Smile Crafters was able to get me in 2 days after I called and I have already been taken care of.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sandi Plattner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQ47ogQ4jSntHFHdW4jhduBjP04Mjs5JFTlqa1C2tCzIUNJ_A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Going to the dentist has got to be right up there w/publis speaking as something most people don't like to do.  Yet, the staff \u0026 professionals at Monarch have eliminated my apprehension/fear/dread of these necessary appointments; and, I now actually look forward to my next appointment!\n\nYou expect professionalism from any medical office, but professionalism doesn't calm your anxiety.   I've been going to Monarch for the last three yrs; and, their staff are very warm, friendly \u0026 caring people who have put my fears to rest.  For ME to say all this speaks volumes as I used to be the biggest chicken when it came to dentistry.\n\nGive Monarch a try, you'll be glad you did!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"T McLain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLucOQtBrIn76Ecm0DzOj00Qx8EyHUmlIJd4vG16Tm67IQrdA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After a horrible experience with another nationally recognized dental group, I found Smiles.  I was treated with respect and listened to.  I was advised that I indeed had a broken tooth which explained all my pain that I had been experiencing over the last 10 days and NOT an infection in my gums. Dr. Hayek and his assistant were exceptional and addressed what was causing excruciating pain and then offered advice addressing other issues I had going on. I walked out pain free, until the numbing wore off of course, but was given something for pain management. I am so happy I found this practice and will definitely tell others about it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lorilee Chynoweth","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWP1Pa9UuzSFLLUQT-aVJCO1A-L0LIGBk