ame":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"ethereumrpr YAKK","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocImuLJCQawTh_4jWJTgdj3-ZUuVgL4G0MHr-vJjxT7CAfraWA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had an appointment scheduled for 1:30 PM and was still sitting in the waiting room at 3:00 PM without being seen. No updates, no explanation, and no effort to communicate how much longer the wait would be.\n\nI understand that medical offices can run behind sometimes, but waiting over an hour past the scheduled appointment with zero communication is unacceptable and disrespectful to patients’ time. I eventually had to leave without being treated.\n\nIf you value punctual appointments or basic communication, I would recommend looking elsewhere.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cristina S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUEIOQge8VnQ-EZ9rwzLelRtHOnJpJ3VJabixP6nQe4LR0d4Do3=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The staff here made me feel so comfortable and not embarrassed about my teeth. The hygienist Taylor was awesome. Dr. Patton and Ridley were efficient and welcoming. Definitely recommend this place to anyone needing dental care","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"S Shaffer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0GkQ_pp4voRUGzjaCNL90xvf4_gIsK-sU745qkpfvFWKRRWQi=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had to get a tooth pulled. The Lady Dentist was able to pull it that day. (New patient) MORE importantly,  I did not have enough to pay the whole bill but promised to pay at end of day. They trusted me. I ended up borrowing from a friend so paid in full before I left. But the fact that they trusted me to come back meant a lot! I've had no issues with the missing tooth.  I recommend!!\nS.Shaffer","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gabe G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKH2Z1VEger0AhuUwr2Q5JXcMBa5zv9bDIHfDSs53JIlwNNA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have had a great experience across the board at the Aspen Dental San Angelo!  At every level, from the xray techs to the hygienist to the dentist, everyone has been real professional, friendly, and personable.  It makes going to the dentist easy and not traumatic.  Kudos to the San Angelo team for a job well done!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Don Vinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKhLy-qZmRSme5Doo2Th4-8kKCx_EtlJI4jU_0TlCBJ8rNIHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"very friendly, helpful staff.  I has a very \"simple fix\" according to the dentist (I saw her for about 15 seconds) .   It would have been much better if it could've been fixed while I was there instead of waiting for another appt 6 days later.  it would've taken less time overall, for me \u0026 the office,  to fix it while I was already there","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lisa M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzvj8FaUN35O5Cem-E3XqoOr7sB3tma9aV9Rb-0KKC1LnmlgQ1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was a new patient to Aspen dental. I honestly was a little worried because I have only gone to private practice dentist.  From the time I walked in, the receptionist made me feel welcome and was so sweet, then Evelyn did all my x-rays and was awesome and sweet also, then I saw Dr. Cantu and I knew at that point I had gone to the right place. She was very efficient and straight forward, didn't say I needed a bunch of stuff done (just excatally what I went for) she explained everything very thoroughly and was very sweet also.  I then saw the dental hygenist (I don't remember her name, tall slender woman) she explained everything and went over what I needed done. I then saw the office manager (I believe her name is Marisa) she also was so sweet, went over the cost of everything I am going to need done, but didn't rush me at all to schedule an appointment to get it done and let me know what appointments were available to get all my work done and let me decide if I wanted to schedule or not.   I do have to get a front tooth pulled and a bone graft, and a temporary partial.  I really wanted it done asap and she explained that if I got it done on the Friday I was there I wouldn't have my partial the same day because the techs leave early on Fridays and she explained that she didn't recommend getting in done the next Monday or Tuesday (because I will be going out of town on Wednesday) and she didn't want me to end have having an issue with the partial and be out of town.  I really appreciated her letting me know all of that.  I also have to have 2 other top teeth pulled and will end up getting a bridge. I was only really worried about 2 teeth and then take care of the 3rd later, she explained to me I should go ahead and get all 3 pulled so they only make one bridge instead of 2 or 3 bridges split into several appointments.  she went over what it would all cost and I set the appointment that worked for me and didn't feel rushed to make an appointment or rushed to get it done quickly (especially since it is costly).  She help me with payment plans and then went ahead and had my impressions done so my partial would be ready as soon as my teeth were pulled and wouldn't have to wait a couple hours on my appointment day.\nI left actually feeling good about needing the work done.  I as most do not like to go to the dentist and usually the prices of treatment is what will keep me away.   I am actually excited to finally get this work done.  So far I highly recommend this Aspen dental.  Every person I came in contact with was very professional, sweet and knowledgeable.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Wendy Walters Poss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAj1j6SnHL5Oa4uJgT8fz1Tkvc5idUmUn__HFk8PKMLhF8Nw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Who EVER has a great visit to the dentist?  Everyone was pleasant and helpful. Was not satisfied with them not offering instructions on how long not to eat or what I could eat after this first visit for a crown.  No mention about post pain or what to do if the temporary crown chipped pieces off.  No mention about the fact that I'm a nite grinder and what I should do. Otherwise it was a blast.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeff Hutcherson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuY84ijQ-fsAZkQznYjcXmIvQRWIGeB7vufl1SVgeZGr8h21U=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went in for a complex dental solution consultation and it went very smooth!  Worked with Jordyn, Ridley and Dr Cantu and they've proven that I made the right choice to pick Aspen Dental.  Looking forward to further interactions on a \"maintenance\" cadence vs the work I need to have completed.  I feel like I'm in good hands and have nothing to worry about going forward.  Awesome team and very easy to work with!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
