experience, very clean office, nice people!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sonny Armintrout","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKj2ujYS1qwmjS9Yde7OlUDSJruyDaVUuXpZtFmTOQhzsnXsA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Very nice white lady at the desk. The form s were meaningless for X-Rays, at least 20 pages or more for a 78 year old man who has suffered a stroke in the past. The white lady did help me out after my complaining about the non sense. The assistant was very rude and did not show elderly people knowledge. The Dentist was the same as the assistant, he was maybe worse. The office was very dry and gave off bad vibes. Most likely Will only return to get my X-Rays.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn04FABYXO2Nv_4IPaeL2cE50jpMHLG02q6bdxO4hIrh1PSl6mlPooRVHwXFMC_8R52dJbEa4e58TE3aQhbX1CnCtc1q8x5fDi3v5y9y7E3Y5QWUM9EAYzwYILmqCDr8mB9kzYo3tU85CvYD=k-no"],"When":"2025-8-29"},{"Name":"David GsTA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLBOEUmiggz-SERsxmyy5et6vVWK1c2zTS4_m6PxJukd6TCxA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a great experience at this dental office! Savannah, the hygienist, was so professional and kind, and Britney at the front desk was very sweet and professional as well, i felt at home. The whole team made me feel comfortable from start to finish. Also, a Big shout out to the Doc and Veronica too—everyone was wonderful. Truly smiles that last forever! I will be back soon!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kristy West","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrZchnlcfv1klpMHOKIiX0mkjSlBSzOxDCVtgt5Oi8R0tHbw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My friend had a three hour appointment with iv sedation so I had to wait out front.\n\nThe desk girls were nice, but one was extremely loud every time she said something. Like LOUD, boisterous talking /laughter at the same time. Between phone calls it was just incessant, loud babbling. There was a patient that came in while I was sitting here that was checking on the status of his insurance coverage. She was basically giggling and laughing while explaining to him the entire time that this insurance would pay for the crown, but not the buildup underneath and that they didn’t approve his IV sedation. Why should I know this just from sitting in the waiting room!?  He was obviously extremely concerned and didn’t look like he was feeling great and it’s like she was just laughing the whole time… So inappropriate.\n\nI also needed to work while waiting, and it was total sensory overload! They had really ridiculous comments just before answering the phone almost every time it rang, (“Oh my God”, “What’s going on with these phones”, “Why are the phones ringing, ringing, ringing?”) there’s music in the back, the TV is on, and then that added on top of their extremely loud talking, mostly one of the ladies, it was just too much to sit in here to get any work done while I was waiting. Just constant babbling. It was too much to listen too without trying to work. And I can tell you names and problems of a few other patients who walked in while I was waiting. That’s definitely not okay!\n\nI’m not even a patient, but just dealing with being present in the waiting area was too much for me!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jamie Young","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQWt7PgmRFUXLMAGSgo23T6eb78EQXY-dswrq-qIYTeM-42g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was sent there by the VA. One of the worst dental experience ever. I was sent there for a bridge, and they got it wrong three times far as matching the color. Dr. Long was my doctor. Everything was a rush rush with him. Never took his time just back and forth. Running from patient to patient. Doing quick fast work, not quality work and the office manager, Tiffany told me they can't keep doing the bridge over and over for as trying to match color my teeth. But at the same time they can't keep just getting it wrong. The last time I went also had one more crown needed to be done along with the bridge. And ridiculously when I got there they couldn't find the other crown that needed to be put on at the time. So when I went back to the VA the VA had to outsource me elsewhere to get the work done correctly. I would not recommend this place again. Never again for me. Also walked around with a temporary bridge and a temporary crown for months until I got it done right by another dentist.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
