h3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJRXiOKC6kB3ypisFkv4pRc_kYnDl2gKbrByy8OMX--hAt62Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Before I came to 1488 dental I was kicked out of 109 other Dentist places, but it was never my fault. I came to 1488 dental cause they promised me that they will purify my White teeth, and gas my brown and black teeth. Mr Okwen with his pale White skin, light blue eyes, and blonde hair did just that.\n\nThank you 1488 dental for securing the existence of my smile and a future for my White teeth.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKmsYr4GqZq4pfmL5mqppx6K4jRP_BGWztEzS25J7frK0wTKAM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Came here for an emergency root canal on 3/28/2025. Things seemed great at first…Scheduled an appt that morning and arrived early that afternoon. I was in the dental office chair for 6.5 hours. No exaggeration. By no means at all should a root canal have taken that long. Every single time I thought we were wrapping up there was something else that needed to be done. It would’ve been helpful if the endodontist relayed exactly what he was going to do before he actually did it. I had to ask for goggles to shield water,etc from going on my face and in my eyes. The endodontist also worked without an assistant and I was left unattended multiple times throughout the dental procedure when dental tools on and inside of my mouth.\n\nCommunication is also poor. You will need to call both phones, leave emails and go back in office just to actually get prescriptions sent and answers to your dental questions. I had extreme facial swelling post procedure due to the numbing agent used and also from my mouth and how being open for such an extended period of time. You are not made a priority. I understand having to leave for personal emergencies unexpectedly but adequately relay that to patients. Communication is key!\n\nDr. Okwen was caring and seemed like he was trying his best but more structure is required from the team overall to have a better patient experience. He couldn’t focus on the dental procedure bc he was helping the front desk every other minute and giving reminders throughout. That’s unacceptable. Front desk staff also needs more training. I’ll be honest, 1488 doesn’t give legitimate. At all. I didn’t want to have to write this detailed review but it’s necessary. That’s just the truth. This dental office also doesn’t accept any type of insurance or copay cards. Very expensive. I understand that there are “emergency” fees that are added on. I get it but excessive is excessive.\n\nI’m able to complete this review only because I finally received the numbing agent that was utilized I’m relaying to my general dentist that I had an allergic reaction to. A patient should not have to delay writing a review to ensure that previously requested dental information is adequately relayed.\n\nI gave this dental office a chance bc I was in need but I do NOT recommend and advise to go elsewhere for overall proper dental care.\n\nI was an actual dental patient at 1488 Dental and I am speaking on my actual experience.\n\n***Update: 6/12\n\nThis was a review from my personal experience. My dentist NEVER received my dental records that were “previously faxed” by this office. I called in office to follow-up with the dental office manager on the phone. We both reviewed documents supposedly sent that day and nothing populated. No accountability and no follow-up. I truly have no reason to lie. Also, my dentist literally had to ask if 1488 put the OLD crown back on!!! There is already a hole in a brand new expensive crown! How is that possible if just placed in April?! Save yourself the time and go elsewhere. Trust this review. Again, I do NOT recommend this dental office from MY personal experience. This Google review is actual and factual. I will give credit when credit is due. This dental experience was not the case.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3v7liIn4dq_iIqffacJHRX7w5zSlpw8kfKDTuzelJ8-qHb4aVSC7xXZIxMuBWtBNvmz0R0YmkBw4dgxhq1kUGdCQ9_y1NL7r5z9yNTsy-kzTTnJ_dcVBovab6qazxlfcWnw0pk=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2-Dl81y2nvz5n2SX6ug2tca5COXEk5hOZ3Iw_ipl1EdxgxVyRmzQ5wX5Ih5epUxih20WuFwExmGkqenfmqiFlwbaCOimLeMmaVFlOyraKPYuTSKo1lwIn1i07Hhw4KuwJOsWGIPQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3TIRm-T9GwzH7hm7jDz6xj7fQ77LLpNln-1UpW6qX9iBTpAa9gf0uxvzncJN_nY-v2Nd8pzribvlPSzjsiCTuwed-myzxEgY5-AVUTOggxDor3j1ee0iJt8WjDmaaXEZxQmzlR=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2Pexw3afeDfECvyhDZsNW6lXQSDGm20qa9b8K6UysIDLMWHnY35bzZSneX-XAlcqA2FehStvShlw-oB7npIqv10NKsa1nSBIfU7jRqb7TaffH8xugGgrJ2OWA9Kam5FjeZJegSQA=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1_9UAM7BW5nmytqvdodvTuFclgps3h7XaH4RArnjPGDmUu88nSSaiL989aLvdFeTXRvxa5hJymOzSiRdMUCmSihB_5cVYEyP0wv_XCM7MI611H6fR8-0cmo3Siwwkl1Q5X4Ok=k-no"],"When":"2025-5-5"},{"Name":"Shaye Dorn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL6dZpk3jlPdZgQYBYpG9zGR4oa_2rtHxGz7tJ43cn6-5i2HH0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had horrible experience here.\nI am sharing my experience so other patients can make informed decisions.\n\nI came in for a filling that had fell out was not clearly informed that I had a cavity on the tooth adjacent to the one being treated. At no point was I told I had a cavity, shown my X-rays, or had the issue explained to me. The dentist later stated that he “told me,” but that is not accurate. He asked a general question about whether I felt any other teeth were affected, and I answered no — because I am not a dentist and had not been informed of a cavity. Asking a patient a question is not the same as diagnosing, explaining findings, and obtaining informed consent.\n\nAfter the filling, I noticed what I believed was damage to the neighboring tooth and returned to have it evaluated. Only then was I told that it was a cavity that had been visible on my X-ray. This was the first time that information was clearly communicated to me.\n\nThe procedure itself was very uncomfortable. I was sprayed with water multiple times, bumped in the head, and given injections without numbing gel, despite me confirming with the assistant that the gel was safe for my allergy after reviewing the ingredients. The wedge placement was extremely rough and painful, and my gums bled throughout the night and remained sore afterward.\n\nWhen I asked if the situation could be made right, the dentist refused. After I stated that I would be sharing my experience publicly, I was accused of blackmail and told that he was uncomfortable continuing my care.\n\nPatients deserve clear communication, transparency, and respectful treatment. Unfortunately, that was not my experience here.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"JReece26","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUn9hLdcPuvDb9bDv5CvxLiNVYNojtwH9RVuBw5Y5YlhpNTbPk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"One thing for certain do not come here. They know how to work the insurance system to get their money for sure. This was my first and last time coming to this dentist.  I went in for my routine cleaning and exam that you are supposed to get done, which according to my wife and our insurance is completely covered and would cost me $0. They asked me when I first walked in, “where is the problem?” I was taken back by that because I haven’t mentioned any problems and wanted a routine cleaning and exam to make further steps. Even my wife was suspicious of the question. Once I was in the chair I was trying to tell the dentist what my concerns were and I wanted a plan for my whole mouth, which would have to have a routine exam first to have a conclusion. The dentist did not exam my mouth but one tooth, took an X-ray of that one tooth and gave me the most ridiculous news that the tooth would need a crown and root canal. Which I know is wrong because it doesn’t hurt nor is it sensitive. I did not receive my routine exam and I did not receive my cleaning and I got charged $50. Come to find out through my insurance benefits they claimed I was in for a problem area only, which was not the case. They are scammers and only want money.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shelly Henderson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL54SzzBck44fR8HApM9EDgPUe7ZOEYYxMiSDaT6bpZxSJ7zg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the smoothest tooth extraction I have ever had. I did not even feel any that \"pressure\". No gas was given - it was not necessary.  The numbing techniques he used did the trick. I personally like the fact that is a small dental office - a receptionist,  an assistant and Dr. Okwen- so yes it is not the fancy dental chain  and I was leary at first and almost did not go in, but I am so glad I did!!!  He has a very calming presence, very personable and likeable. Dr. Okwen and the lovely- patient  receptionist both took time to try undo the knots in my necklace that I had caused due to anxiety. That extra step means alot. And the my took my insurance  so the cost was where it should it have been. I will be going back to have other work done.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gene holrod","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKf1Npb4CtevVQMOO61DY2hv-atcUl64xJxTkq-ye5OsdJDqw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went in on a Sunday with an old root canal that was infected. It ran up my sinus cavity to my eye.  The doctor took me in immediately and removed the old crown and pins completely by himself.  I've never seen that ever.  He was extremely nice and knowledgeable. I'm very thankful he was open on a Sunday because it's rare. I can tell he honestly cares about people and that's also rare.  I'm very grateful.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"chichi2472001","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHLjLPtjC1H0PF1RdT8ECYsqTkBVSAg-IO5Y47_tnWKyxvow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My wife was suffering from a severe toothache after regular office hours, and 1488 Dental was the only place open that could help. We are incredibly grateful they were available! The dentist who treated her was extremely professional, kind, and thorough. He took the time to clearly explain the procedure and made sure she felt comfortable throughout the process. The cost was surprisingly affordable, especially for an emergency visit. We are beyond pleased with the care she received and will definitely recommend 1488 Dental to anyone in need of quality dental services—especially when it matters most!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"TheDemonLord47","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3jjz-uPe1xE9ayVArFhg-US7Zgd1RGW5uf2BqiWDtDoPRsDZq=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went here in August of last year. Needed an emergency crown and at first everything seemed smooth with getting the crown, but when sent to make the crown, and it not fitting right. One of my upper teeth was shaved down that was perfectly healthy to make the crown fit. Now a year later I went to another dentist and was told that I have an opening for bacteria and that the crown was not sealed properly. Of course it would be cheaper to come back here but it is a waste of money and my time to ever go back. Takeaway, does more harm than good. Don’t ever go to this dentist. Due to the lack of empathy from the doctors office I don’t need a response from them, I understand all this was a choice but I thought this was a place to have problems fixed not made worse while also spending thousands of dollars.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
