n, and had surprisingly comfortable furniture. My dental hygienist, Wendy,  was absolutely out of this world! I have never had a more thorough cleaning in my life. 💗 The dentist was polite and down to earth. At no point did the appointment feel rushed or like I was occupying a spot on an assembly line. I’m so thankful I stumbled upon Abilene Family Dentistry. 💗💗💗💗","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Julie Barber","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbRCyupzYVAnXLFNZJxjOyl4ImjDBciyY7jkVd5hUIbN_W91dmlQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent care, innovative and highly skilled dentistry. The dental hygienist is caring and respectful. All around great place to trust with your teeth!!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2YnmvJh0UFxMyrWTJ-cc6ghsXy-QkUVajwpyWXX8I23DEIQuJ-UpqyBEaaUmudFfUBWYQymHDip0RATFhVrUxxkKDhNmRqcS4wSs08VQqVzOXD09AVdRh1MRrfR6VVMoO5ztUITrvNinNw=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-15"},{"Name":"Avery Rodriguez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFj_ymSzPaIclLdv4ecMLsfuosW5KcZB2lR4zO-Jzw2x7c2-_0TQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve always had a fear of going to the dentist, but my recent visit completely changed that thanks to Wendy Sigler. She was absolutely amazing! From the moment I sat in the chair, she walked me through every step of the process with kindness, patience, and care. She made sure I felt comfortable the entire time, checked in with me often, and explained everything clearly. Not only was she incredibly thorough in her work, and did a fantastic job, but her warm personality made the whole experience so much easier. I truly appreciate the extra time and compassion she showed me. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Luis Aguilar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXWBw3EY-yLSTc9xGADk7XTgoJZMYM6HiT3dM6akxU3qqXYs8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The staff at Abilene Family Dentistry are wonderful. They greet you with a smile and provide a relaxing and clean environment. The staff are very informative about the procedures, but also take the time to listen to your concerns or questions. Dr. Webb and his staff have a top-notch dentistry practice. I would highly recommend them!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jocelyn Furr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJubpJWpyCXmolM34B2gXNPILzCRt_6OPDJKewUgy0Wt4n3dw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Apparently the technology system got switched over from a prior system. No information transferred from the old to the new system. And within the new system, there was no transfer of information within a family. This meant that I spent over an hour filling out forms for me and my kids putting mostly the same information in repeatedly: address, insurance, etc.\nThe actual time with the dentist and dental hygienist went well. But I hope in the future, information can more easily be transferred from previous forms to current forms and from one patient in a family to another.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kendal Marshall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9rnqvPsvsntAaF0EdwrBPVdrNkiMyL7atnWXalrN0jM9H34WLwg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I contacted Abilene Family Dental South regarding a dental emergency and initially spoke with the receptionist. Shortly after, I received a call back from the “office manager”, claiming she was listening to the call. She accused me of cursing at the receptionist—something that did not happen. She then gave her two cents, talking to me sideways, saying she wasn’t going to let me disrespect her staff. Again, I did not direct use any inappropriate language toward her, nor was I yelling or being disrespectful.\n\nWhile I may have expressed frustration using a cuss word due to being in significant pain, it was not aimed at the receptionist. I am also recently postpartum, which understandably affected my tone during the call. If the call had been reviewed objectively, it would clearly reflect this.\n\nUnfortunately, instead of reviewing the call and addressing the situation fairly, (lied) I was automatically accused of behavior that did not occur and spoken to in a dismissive and unprofessional manner. Ironically, during the follow-up call, I did give an example of what “cussing and yelling” sounded like—something very different from how I conducted myself initially.\n\nI do not expect to receive services from this office moving forward, but I felt it was important to share my experience so others are aware of how sensitive and dishonest the staff is.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Levi Wilson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQKiljF1pecEW8X-yrX18L6khBu9whGVoQxU3TrurBScJpa8EQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I always enjoy getting my teeth cleaned and my dental hygienist did a great job. She was very informative on how drinking coffee all day with creamer in it is bad for my teeth because of the sugar which I did not realize. Also I am nervous about a root canal and she was able to comfort me into not being afraid about getting that taken care of.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joshlyn Dendy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCd-imNl6RfQjhEglrTFhgSz9z9Zg2AMTohfy4tJt2BLbWQqOlQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have to say everyone was so very helpful and efficient! Monze made my whole experience even better. I went in with nerves and she had the most calm spirit to her. And then Dr. Nicolds went above and beyond and explained everything to me. Both ladies made this dental experience better than I could have imagined.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
