 a referral) and then I need another appointment to do the test. Also, the staff told me that they only see patients who would like to continue their treatment at the UT dentists. So, in short, they only care for people who can be used as cash cows, and not actually to treat them properly. What a disgrace and at the same time, confusing!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Vishal Mistry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWeaF8nqKlojYHkwytkDFrx5bXypnvwGUe8A7NTZro_VdkVV9w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was charged for missing an appointment that I hadn’t confirmed and they still charged me anyways. I put a request to reverse charge due to financial reasons and manager is so irresponsible that she doesn’t care to respond to the email until 2 months and no follow ups. Furthermore the office operator was down rude when I called, saying it’s your fault since you didn’t show up when I told her I hadn’t confirmed and was in a remote location at work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jo W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUV8fhCvSmXTG84akkrFBJT34Q1hrMpx50Qtm2n5FMunF2bEm74=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Received a call back to schedule an appointment after submitting a request online .I Missed the call. I called the scheduling department the representative I spoke with had an unprofessional tone and asked questions under knowledgeable of proximity. She lead the conversation by asking what department I was scheduling in. How am I supposed to know? So I replied with dentistry.To which she responded with “the whole building was dentistry .”The right question to ask an inquiring patient will be what procedure do you want to receive and then provide said information on that department. The rest of the conversation was snarky. Please retrain your representatives on customer service and how to properly triage a call. Hopefully the rest of the experience will go better than the initial phone call .","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Carlos Arocha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpWaQwvIyQ0D1hpgf2h23lwJGip8EaMkxCT3D2BT8oKf-eGGki=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I will submit 2 reviews. One very lousy and another one to the doctor which is an excellent professional worth taking the trip from Katy to Houston.\nThis one review is for the lousy and disorganized administration services when one checks in. They did not have the insurance information on file and they did not bother to check at the time of scheduling the appointment blaming on me for not providing that information. It is the first time it happens with a medical provider, the insurance information is always checked at scheduling the appointment.\nWe decided to never come back. It is a real shame because Dr. Alejandro Aponte is one of the best odontologists in Houston.\nVery unhappy patient.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mayra Ivonne Leonard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJBQElbShiYgvq39LdXc9F2uduhhpe2S1954Ng9ayzmOcKeUKwYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an exceptional visit at UT Dentists with my daughter! We had appointments for a new patient check-up, cleaning, and filling replacement—all done in a single day. The staff, provider, and dental hygienist were friendly, welcoming, and professional. The facility was impeccably clean and well-presented. Grateful to have found a dental office that truly prioritizes patient care. Any previous negative experiences were completely overshadowed by the exceptional service at UT Dentists. Looking forward to our future visits! My daughter was also very impressed by the quality of care and the thorough answers to her dental health inquiries.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"AKS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPAbjVcNOoISTDa1EqoLCEIBYsSYzuz9dsiHy6_ldEcbSGeJQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"UT Dentist Private Practice clinics in my experience is over all not a good place to obtain dental care because of high cost, non caring attitudes of the front office and billing section and poor care of some of the dental doctors who don’t explain well, don’t discuss the options and possible complications of procedures and poor follow up instructions and pain management. One would expect great care being a university setting but this practice is far from it. Just shop around until you find a good dentist and a clinic.\n\nFollow up:\n\nI emailed the Manager as instructed to address my grievances and after a reminder a week, no response! The clinic promised a refund (broke my tooth and incomplete treatment) but after 4 weeks no refund which I need to pay for another dental clinic that fixed their mishap! What an irresponsible group of people!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Albert Stevens","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK53rro9mGbTfOtBKST0MphAU131NztqhzMBjPnqc5P1dX0-g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have been trying to get an appointment for my child for the last 6 months or so! I’ve called multiple times and the answering service have taken my messages. I’ve also called and left messages on their voicemail and no one has called me back! This is so ridiculous and unacceptable but UT is supposed to b number one! You guys are horrible!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lynn Wooten","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLl-IXMxjIE5N54tAdJHjilWiD6APRm88Wev0RgrdejLhjnyw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The service and cost, great. My student Tala very patient and listens to me no rush. She's the best.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
