was seeing and speak intelligently with the staff. I could have had my tooth pulled the same day but I opted to come back a few days later. I had a virtually painless and super fast extraction and im really happy with my visit, service ...everything and everyone. ❤️ I plan to come back and allow u to take care of the other side as well.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2GHDSBhYepPY2eKD4WN_aGF4Q-FuDz0fY-rBYxk7IJO8tVQc-7T_dI7T4v8IJ446TOxO33RYIhwWMoZ9zqGz0Pas1kGUhHmfC-8_eVZfsEMOmoDHCAgPDTcBWW5qXKuNjBqLMXPmSleNFD=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0z-tCV1gTiLPJ8Hd2NfrujGISsOXBs7tBenpzjTovmnGZog1DZn5lailaPCoBSd76F1sv0QpJcCdBTYdlVQPXFTvKj4b7a3DJQjDKBXKVbEqCPdpzxJSXokNXzg1z0EQn4DT0LBW-J397S=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0HPPaHw9bTkL7RRCGt9eB_EzO_G-a-2sCX8FmW5jnDKL4W09mFv_qUl-is7dbEkr_xT-LoBuKaHTea_KtdBx_CzR9vi7YrbbSUuRPX66PPXuu5pZtoiJvFmGdlFWqMVAlvVLWAcsA70EA=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-26"},{"Name":"Susan Johnson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ-bZRLlATDJXtCE-1jLOdpfnHYYtDZNHAl-cnHkJrQxddNtA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I had dental insurance over 20yrs ago but now (just over broke) jobs no longer have it or offer it.  plan offered by a dentist was expensive to get and use so like cash pay.\nMy brother had his wisdom teeth removed here 12 years ago and happy with the services.\nNow I've been trying to make an appt for a 7-9 mos? now. Using the portal and leaving msgs. I finally spoke to someone today and she was courteous and told me to call back in 2wks.\nSorry for the long back story.\nIts a wakeup call to how the work economy health/dental environment has changed. Its not the dental college fault for being over over worked, its companies dropping out of employees basic care. So I will appreciate any, all my services when finally getting a chance.. Who has $$600-800-$1200. for teeth cleanings? Not services just cleanings. Be kind their staff is  doing the best possible care to help students get training while offering low cost dental care to the public.  Thanks!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"F. Garcia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCldyOnHqgz0LuKbEgJxjnaxFAkIIRuhU43qs4LlARI4yZdYIlkg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the pleasure of being Jaqueline Martinez's patient these past few weeks and she did great! I have really bad anxiety and Jacqueline along with Professor King made me feel comfortable during the entire process, talked me through it and explained everything they were doing so I would be aware of what was happening. They both continued to make sure I was doing ok the entire time which helped ease my anxiety. Thank You Jacqueline Martinez and Professor King!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nina Ali","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLNY0XkXpwXtlC2ZS7psTbGLiZj5ACbQDGrnRvrT3Rid-kOhg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"ALERT: STAY AWAY AT ALL COSTS!\nI strongly advise anyone to avoid this practice at all costs. Our experience with UTHealth Houston School of Dentistry has been nothing short of distressing. We took our son for a procedure, and he ended up enduring unnecessary pain because the initial treatment plan was incorrect. The procedure was halted midway, and we were then told we needed an entirely different treatment. This caused not only physical discomfort for our child but also a financial burden, as we were charged over $300 out-of-pocket for the erroneous initial treatment despite having insurance coverage.\n\nIn addition, we were given contradictory information by a staff member named Sandra (a horrible person who know nothing about customer service), who insisted on details that conflicted with what our insurance company confirmed directly to us. She placed me on hold for over 20 minutes and never returned to the call, repeatedly saying she would call back and never doing so. She continued to provide incorrect and contradictory financial information but always sounded confident in her understanding out of insurance and coverages (even though she didn’t). This unprofessional conduct has made an already difficult situation even worse.\n\nIn summary, the mishandling of our son’s care, the financial losses, and the poor communication and accountability are unacceptable. I hope this feedback helps others avoid similar frustrations and encourages the clinic to improve its standards.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Antasia Monroe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHeeIzG4hNOHIMqvztRYFwdOaCMqOYI5AN4Z2KXBY4dURVk9U2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I expected the worst, but my experience with Kaysie, a third-year dental student, exceeded all expectations. She demonstrated the skill and confidence of an experienced dentist, thoughtfully exploring the best solution for my condition and ensuring we reached a satisfactory outcome.\nKaysie was thorough and attentive, taking the time to explain each part of my exam in a way that was easy to understand.\n\nHer warm, humorous personality made the appointment comfortable and enjoyable—we laughed the entire time. I truly believe our engaging conversation added to the positive experience. Based on her exceptional skills and the professor’s praise of her abilities, I would confidently return to Kaysie for future dental care. She is truly deserving of recognition for her outstanding work. 🤏🏾 Clock it  Kaysie F. 🦷","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dzina Rabtsevich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTDXUbzPG5yrs4wIta2B040ssk0GP-DqMl4bNmPHH2_20T86F1dg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The students Brandon and Deena did an excellent job! I highly recommend them. I came with my children (ages 7 and 11), and the work was outstanding — beyond my expectations!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0YPSwFaSRpRj8I9lG6vPp-44AjAtX76v63vPgAFFGFAFsgJd6OObwYh55JA942dje0kRfW_s1YBJBlVmlGjv5KSQGNJwNPie5_XsOFCbBzaHysasTHphY7e7Ry4go-fiAL1Td-xFTi3bk=k-no"],"When":"2025-9-25"},{"Name":"Josselin Reynoso","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZdisYQu11inW2ip-niYhKI4D-JdaPYm7uKEZMR2VZN1Fy-xE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Submitted my info and was contacted within a week. Appointment was scheduled for 3 weeks out due to my availability. I went in for root canal retreatment due to infection. dr Kodra was GREAT. Cleaned thoroughly, explained everything during the process. Also made sure to tell me what to expect. No pain, no meds(infection was cleaned out well). Insured it was cleared out during th process as well doing scans repeatedly. Highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sherman On","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXf0XzJ-eWXAg0wMyuQNKyyRUUHyGEtQY2Be3SSZmKXtBwdyluS9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing experience for my mother-in-law! Note: she needed lots of work: 2 extractions, gum work, couple fillings and crowns. The costs are superb! Appointments do take longer than normal so plan accordingly. Parking across the street is not free. I highly recommend this place.  Remember they are learning so exercise your patience","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2EZa5TKndM_YIzSe08AdA3_bt9QJgpV1v_u6uGg_UNY5oe8BnAuEV4HlVN4g12O5uKIB6eLf5K6-R8wlmNPvfKoh95ktC4v6R9mYR_nb7eoODdc1O_qOhdpy1UDvAEIzYJ_t8D=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1gZy5v-WZ9AhtUjkkx5_rZ6vR7oNHpskrueLG6-oat-_gJJYA6KjSqRtoMrZgQn__1EGXoFNKT4Z28qwuVk81h5ulYFabIgYjsZw1wMz8BbpV_bC6sr4FSrKcSneqvtXEXYBqR=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0MPIvYEPmsZ9npiTMO-6Gla65DEr1QOk6A313c0oLAANui9E8X59rKRoycEonbu2VRAobD9064ACyeUB4tTjruNSa3xyuPcsle7qU8uiDMx7RZot6zEvk7ZkH6w3yixnlqG-l4=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2twlps9PE4Wr6Fx1SmckGOMN4qsrlQSacaBQrRT5r0Ju5VAp28btR